WEBVTT

00:26.394 --> 00:28.527
[ Dramatic music plays ]

00:28.529 --> 00:32.331
Welcome to "Sports Now,"
live coverage of pro draft 2018.

00:32.333 --> 00:33.732
With less than a minute
left on the clock,

00:33.734 --> 00:35.334
all eyes are on Miami
for their picks.

00:35.336 --> 00:36.735
Who are you guys looking to
on this pick?

00:36.737 --> 00:38.771
Oh, I'm going Rich Porter
all day long.

00:38.773 --> 00:40.572
I mean, in this draft,
he's the guy.

00:40.574 --> 00:43.175
He's the man.
He's got all the tools, guys.

00:43.177 --> 00:45.210
Listen, he's got
the athletic ability.

00:45.212 --> 00:46.578
He's got the mobility.

00:46.580 --> 00:48.480
He's got ambidextrous
arm strength, guys.

00:48.482 --> 00:50.215
There's no other choice
right here.

00:50.217 --> 00:52.151
What about these reports
of his throwing temper tantrums

00:52.153 --> 00:54.186
or having emotional outbursts?

00:54.188 --> 00:56.255
His maturity is going to be
the biggest challenge

00:56.257 --> 00:57.756
to his career at this point,

00:57.758 --> 00:59.558
but I think he's up for it,
right?

00:59.560 --> 01:01.260
He's been through a lot
in his life,

01:01.262 --> 01:02.795
and I think that, once again,

01:02.797 --> 01:05.397
he'll have to prove his way
through this situation.

01:05.399 --> 01:07.266
But with the right coaching,

01:07.268 --> 01:09.301
with the right team
surrounding him,

01:09.303 --> 01:11.703
I think
he can grow into this league

01:11.705 --> 01:14.373
as a player and as a person.

01:14.375 --> 01:15.841
All right.
Here it is.

01:15.843 --> 01:17.643
Let's go to the podium
for the official selection

01:17.645 --> 01:19.244
of this year's draft picks.

01:19.246 --> 01:22.448
For our first-round pick,
Miami selects...

01:22.450 --> 01:25.784
Rich Porter, quarterback,
West Colorado.

01:25.786 --> 01:29.088
But the real question now is,
where <i> is</i> Rich Porter?

01:30.291 --> 01:32.558
[ Telephone rings ]

01:33.260 --> 01:36.128
[ Gasps, sighs ]

01:36.130 --> 01:38.130
[ Ringing continues ]

01:47.842 --> 01:50.476
[ Ringing continues ]

01:50.478 --> 01:52.611
[ <i> Beep</i> ]

01:52.613 --> 01:54.179
HARDWICK: <i> Rich Porter.</i>

01:54.181 --> 01:56.782
<i>This is Coach Hardwick
with Miami.</i>

01:56.784 --> 01:59.318
<i>A time like this, I thought
you'd be glued by your phone.</i>

01:59.320 --> 02:03.622
<i>Anyway, I hope you love good
weather and beautiful women</i>

02:03.624 --> 02:07.693
<i>because you are playing
for me now, so call me back.</i>

02:07.695 --> 02:09.761
[ <i> Beep</i> ]

02:12.333 --> 02:13.765
ANDY: <i> Hello, Mr. Porter.</i>

02:13.767 --> 02:16.335
<i>This is Andy
from the Cebu Rescue Unit.</i>

02:16.337 --> 02:18.504
<i>I am calling because
we may have finally found</i>

02:18.506 --> 02:20.239
<i>the remains of your mother.</i>

02:20.241 --> 02:21.740
<i>We need a family member
to come down</i>

02:21.742 --> 02:23.876
<i>and I.D. the body to confirm.</i>

02:23.878 --> 02:26.311
<i>I understand this must
be difficult for you,</i>

02:26.313 --> 02:29.414
<i>but you would only need
to come up for one day.</i>

02:29.850 --> 02:31.850
<i>Please call us
to schedule soon.</i>

02:31.852 --> 02:34.253
<i>Thank you, Mr. Porter.</i>

02:35.322 --> 02:37.356
[ <i> Beep</i> ]

02:37.358 --> 02:39.758
MAN:
<i>Rich, it's your agent again.</i>

02:39.760 --> 02:41.593
<i>Listen, I know
you're dealing with a lot,</i>

02:41.595 --> 02:43.929
<i>and I'm sure you have
a good reason for disappearing.</i>

02:43.931 --> 02:46.665
<i>I'll work on buying us
some time here Stateside.</i>

02:46.667 --> 02:49.735
<i>In the meantime, I hope you
find what you're looking for...</i>

02:49.737 --> 02:52.204
<i>- wherever you are.</i>
- [ Beep ]

02:56.310 --> 02:58.877
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

03:29.710 --> 03:31.476
It's not her.

03:31.478 --> 03:33.579
Are you sure?

03:35.249 --> 03:37.349
Yeah, I'm positive.

03:38.986 --> 03:41.353
I'm sorry, Mr. Porter.

03:46.560 --> 03:48.860
I know you came a long way.

03:49.496 --> 03:52.364
I'm not leaving
until I find her.

03:57.004 --> 03:58.971
I know you understand.

03:58.973 --> 04:01.573
It just helps me cope
to help others.

04:01.575 --> 04:03.008
Mom.

04:03.010 --> 04:05.277
I want you to have this.

04:05.746 --> 04:07.546
It's our birthstone.

04:09.350 --> 04:11.917
BERRY: Porter!

04:11.919 --> 04:14.519
What the hell
do you think this is, huh?

04:14.521 --> 04:16.855
You fall asleep
in my meetings again,

04:16.857 --> 04:19.324
I'm gonna have Jeremiah start
over you. You understand me?

04:19.326 --> 04:21.692
Yo! Go, Miah!

04:22.830 --> 04:26.031
All right.
Today is Media Day, gentlemen,

04:26.033 --> 04:29.701
which means I want everyone
on their best behavior.

04:29.703 --> 04:31.770
We have
some very special visitors

04:31.772 --> 04:33.438
coming from the hospital today,

04:33.440 --> 04:35.474
and I want all of us
to make them feel welcome,

04:35.476 --> 04:36.975
especially in front
of the press.

04:36.977 --> 04:39.711
Coach.
Media? Who's coming?

04:39.713 --> 04:41.847
Sorry, Barnum.
No one big enough to recruit.

04:41.849 --> 04:44.383
Just an ordinary day.

04:44.385 --> 04:46.652
BERRY: All right.
Listen up.

04:46.654 --> 04:49.755
Now is the time
that we show the world

04:49.757 --> 04:52.624
that we are
the toughest men on this planet.

04:52.626 --> 04:54.493
No pads, no helmets,

04:54.495 --> 04:56.695
- but raw aggression.
- MAN: Mm!

04:56.697 --> 04:58.463
- MAN #2: Whoo!
- MAN #3: Yeah.

05:01.769 --> 05:04.036
Fear nothing.
Regret nothing.

05:04.038 --> 05:06.471
- TOGETHER: Regret nothing!
- Achieve everything!

05:06.473 --> 05:07.673
TOGETHER: Achieve everything!

05:07.675 --> 05:09.841
We are the Cebu Saints!

05:09.843 --> 05:12.644
[ Cheers and applause ]

05:23.524 --> 05:24.856
Whoo.

05:24.858 --> 05:26.458
Look sharp, Barnum.

05:26.460 --> 05:28.093
Media's here.

05:28.095 --> 05:29.728
BERRY: So, that's about it --
conditioning,

05:29.730 --> 05:31.396
conditioning, conditioning.

05:31.398 --> 05:32.831
See, last year,
we gave up too easily.

05:32.833 --> 05:34.900
I admit
we burned out too quickly.

05:34.902 --> 05:38.003
We got tired. Don't expect
to see that this season.

05:38.005 --> 05:40.105
RICH: God!
Catch the ball!

05:40.841 --> 05:43.342
- That's how you catch the ball.
- I'm trying. I'm sorry.

05:43.344 --> 05:46.678
No, I don't want to hear that. I
threw this right to your number.

05:46.680 --> 05:48.914
Now catch the damn ball.

05:48.916 --> 05:52.517
- Wake up!
- Any other questions?

05:52.519 --> 05:55.954
I guess the change of scenery
didn't help much, did it?

05:57.558 --> 05:59.691
Ray McQuinn.

06:00.127 --> 06:02.627
What business
do you have here in Cebu?

06:03.797 --> 06:07.099
Well, you know, Rich Porter's
still a big name in the U.S.

06:07.101 --> 06:09.668
Folks wanna know what happened
to Miami's top pick.

06:09.670 --> 06:11.370
You know what happened.

06:11.372 --> 06:13.672
Well, Miami's pissed.

06:13.674 --> 06:15.374
His agent's pissed.
Commish is pissed.

06:15.376 --> 06:18.977
I'm just here to ask
a few questions, nothing more.

06:18.979 --> 06:22.581
No. You're not cashing in
on Rich again.

06:22.583 --> 06:24.049
I'm just trying to write a piece
on why he's here

06:24.051 --> 06:25.617
and not playing ball.

06:25.619 --> 06:28.987
He <i> is</i> playing ball.
And you know why he's here.

06:28.989 --> 06:32.624
And playing here
would solve things. Is that it?

06:32.626 --> 06:35.160
Both of you throw away
professional careers

06:35.162 --> 06:39.531
to come out here and play
with this ragtag team of...

06:39.533 --> 06:42.067
Christ, I don't even know
what you call it.

06:42.870 --> 06:45.437
It's a bit odd.
Wouldn't you say?

06:47.841 --> 06:49.708
That will be all for today,
everyone.

06:49.710 --> 06:51.643
Thank you for coming.

06:55.949 --> 06:59.451
I came to write
a positive piece.

07:00.154 --> 07:02.053
Really?

07:02.689 --> 07:04.523
You're the one
that stabbed him in the back.

07:04.525 --> 07:06.892
And for what?
For what?

07:06.894 --> 07:08.927
A headline and some cash?

07:08.929 --> 07:11.563
You nearly ruined his life.

07:11.999 --> 07:14.166
You make me sick.

07:16.437 --> 07:18.503
So, is that
no on-the-record comment, Coach?

07:18.505 --> 07:21.139
BERRY: Yep, and you can
quote me on that.

07:23.677 --> 07:24.976
I'll be in touch.

07:36.190 --> 07:37.522
DENISE: Mr. Porter.

07:40.594 --> 07:42.794
Would you mind taking a photo?

07:42.796 --> 07:45.664
He's a very big fan of yours.

07:46.567 --> 07:47.799
Sure.

07:50.103 --> 07:52.070
What's your name, kid?

07:53.207 --> 07:55.040
All right.

07:56.577 --> 07:58.477
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

08:04.117 --> 08:06.117
You're welcome.

08:07.888 --> 08:09.988
[ Indistinct conversations ]

08:17.965 --> 08:19.598
Heads up.

08:19.600 --> 08:21.500
Ray's here.

08:35.682 --> 08:38.082
- Hey, jackass.
- What?!

08:38.085 --> 08:39.618
You want to know why Ray's here?

08:39.620 --> 08:41.720
No, I don't,
'cause I don't care.

08:41.722 --> 08:42.953
Well, you should.

08:42.956 --> 08:45.190
- What is your problem?!
- You are!

08:45.192 --> 08:46.791
Big-time reporters are here,

08:46.793 --> 08:48.693
and you're acting like
you don't care at all.

08:48.695 --> 08:52.230
You have any idea what
this could mean for us? Huh?!

08:52.232 --> 08:55.300
Be the <i> captain</i> of this team,
not the <i> tumor.</i>

08:56.603 --> 08:58.670
You think I'm afraid of you?

09:01.141 --> 09:03.842
God help you if you ruin
my chances of getting picked up.

09:08.882 --> 09:10.782
How you doing, Rich?

09:10.784 --> 09:12.984
Go home, Ray.

09:12.986 --> 09:14.886
Listen, buddy, I understand
why you're pissed.

09:14.888 --> 09:17.722
- I do.
- I said, "Go home."

09:17.724 --> 09:20.158
I'm just trying
to make things right here.

09:20.160 --> 09:22.928
You know what?

09:22.930 --> 09:26.798
You come around here
one more time, and you're done.

09:32.306 --> 09:33.672
Everything okay?

09:33.674 --> 09:34.806
- Yeah. Good.
- You sure?

09:34.808 --> 09:37.208
Yeah. Yeah.

09:37.210 --> 09:39.844
Okay? Ready?

09:39.846 --> 09:42.047
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

09:50.223 --> 09:51.957
[ Tape recorder beeps ]

10:18.652 --> 10:20.819
Be careful.

10:23.924 --> 10:27.692
Rich.
You're my hero.

10:29.262 --> 10:31.196
[ Voice breaking ] I'm sorry,
Mom. It should have been me.

10:31.198 --> 10:33.198
No, honey. No.

10:33.200 --> 10:34.833
- [ Crying ]
- Shh.

10:34.835 --> 10:36.735
- Mom, I'm so sorry.
- Stop.

10:41.241 --> 10:43.174
Babe.

10:44.811 --> 10:46.144
Babe!

10:48.382 --> 10:51.983
- What's wrong?
- [ Sighs ]

10:51.985 --> 10:53.284
It's a migraine.

10:53.286 --> 10:55.353
I'm stressed.

10:57.024 --> 10:59.424
I know what you need
to feel better.

11:08.035 --> 11:09.300
Where are you gonna go now?

11:09.302 --> 11:11.102
I gotta go see a guy
about my mom.

11:11.104 --> 11:13.738
Oh.
Do you want me to come with you?

11:13.740 --> 11:16.141
- No. It's okay.
- All right.

11:16.143 --> 11:18.276
I guess we'll celebrate later,
then?

11:18.278 --> 11:19.744
Celebrate what?

11:20.247 --> 11:23.181
Our one-month anniversary.
Remember?

11:23.183 --> 11:25.750
Anniversary.
Right. Um...

11:25.752 --> 11:26.985
What?

11:26.987 --> 11:29.421
N-- I just --
I didn't realize that...

11:29.423 --> 11:31.322
- That we were a thing?
- No, no, no.

11:31.324 --> 11:34.993
I didn't realize
that that day is today.

11:34.995 --> 11:36.828
- Oh. Okay.
- Yeah.

11:36.830 --> 11:38.430
I guess we'll hang out later,
then?

11:38.432 --> 11:40.265
Yeah.
I'll give you a call.

11:40.267 --> 11:41.800
- Okay.
- All right.

11:44.705 --> 11:46.738
[ Engine starts ]

12:12.299 --> 12:16.234
- Hello.
- Hi. Henry?

12:16.236 --> 12:18.303
Rich Porter.
Sorry I'm late.

12:18.305 --> 12:20.305
Yes, Mr. Porter.

12:20.307 --> 12:23.007
Please, sit down.

12:26.947 --> 12:30.148
So, are you a friend of Manny's?

12:30.150 --> 12:34.219
No. Actually, an officer
at the station recommended you.

12:34.221 --> 12:37.122
I'm usually the last resort.

12:37.124 --> 12:39.390
Mm. Well, they said that you
were the best on the island.

12:41.361 --> 12:42.894
How can I help?

12:46.333 --> 12:48.800
My mother, Karen.

12:49.269 --> 12:52.237
She's one of the missing persons
of the typhoon.

12:55.509 --> 12:57.041
I'm sorry to hear that.

12:59.246 --> 13:00.945
When did you last hear from her?

13:00.947 --> 13:05.416
I last contacted her
a week before the disaster.

13:07.320 --> 13:09.554
What was she doing here?

13:09.556 --> 13:12.457
Helping orphanages, feeding
the poor, that type of stuff.

13:12.459 --> 13:14.259
Are you a believer?

13:14.261 --> 13:16.394
No.

13:16.396 --> 13:19.998
Do you think
your mother's still alive?

13:20.000 --> 13:21.966
I'm just looking for closure.

13:21.968 --> 13:24.202
No, I don't think
she's still alive.

13:24.204 --> 13:28.206
Well... if she was in Cebu
during the disaster

13:28.208 --> 13:31.009
and you haven't heard from her
by now,

13:31.011 --> 13:34.813
her body was probably found and
buried by one of the churches.

13:34.815 --> 13:36.414
[ Keyboard clacks,
printer whirring ]

13:36.416 --> 13:38.483
How much is your retainer fee?

13:38.485 --> 13:40.418
I wish I could help you.

13:40.420 --> 13:43.555
If this is about money,
I don't care. I'll pay.

13:44.324 --> 13:46.291
These are just some
of the missing persons

13:46.293 --> 13:48.593
I'm already looking for.

13:48.595 --> 13:52.230
I'm sorry, but I can't take
any new cases at this time.

13:55.602 --> 13:57.969
This is for you.

13:57.971 --> 14:00.872
It's a list of all
the organizations in the area,

14:00.874 --> 14:02.941
including those
that aren't online.

14:02.943 --> 14:04.242
Free of charge.

14:08.381 --> 14:11.850
I saw you looking at
that picture when you came in.

14:11.852 --> 14:14.285
I figure you know who that is.

14:14.287 --> 14:15.920
Samson?

14:15.922 --> 14:18.456
One of the great judges.

14:18.458 --> 14:21.893
A warrior of God
who fought entire armies

14:21.895 --> 14:24.262
and won great battles alone.

14:24.264 --> 14:26.531
Yeah, but Samson
wasn't always strong.

14:26.533 --> 14:28.233
It was just his hair.

14:28.235 --> 14:30.902
It was his fear of being alone
that made him weak.

14:31.371 --> 14:34.305
He lost his strength from a
woman that he thought he loved.

14:34.307 --> 14:37.141
But his strength
eventually returned...

14:37.143 --> 14:41.546
when he truly relied on God
and called out to him.

14:41.548 --> 14:43.481
His strength was his <i> faith.</i>

14:43.483 --> 14:45.516
It had nothing to do
with his hair.

14:46.386 --> 14:49.254
When you need to call on God
for strength...

14:50.090 --> 14:53.992
...I hope you see that he's
closer than you think he is.

14:53.994 --> 14:56.294
I'd like to know
where he is right now.

14:56.296 --> 14:57.395
HENRY: Ask him.

14:58.131 --> 15:02.166
He hears,
and he will answer you.

15:02.168 --> 15:04.035
He loves us like that.

15:04.037 --> 15:08.606
After all, he is a god
of second chances.

15:08.608 --> 15:10.341
Thanks.

15:10.343 --> 15:12.977
There's a number on that,
so if you find any new leads,

15:12.979 --> 15:15.013
don't hesitate to call.

15:19.352 --> 15:21.586
Rich.

15:21.588 --> 15:23.922
Godspeed.

15:28.695 --> 15:30.395
[ Slow music plays,
woman vocalizing ]

15:30.397 --> 15:33.097
[ Door closes ]

15:33.667 --> 15:35.633
[ Door closes ]

15:38.438 --> 15:40.405
TESS: I didn't know
you played the piano.

15:41.341 --> 15:42.440
Were you any good?

15:43.176 --> 15:44.976
What are you doing here?

15:45.979 --> 15:47.946
I told you I was coming over.

15:47.948 --> 15:50.248
I thought I told you to wait
until I called.

15:50.250 --> 15:53.251
I know,
but I made you something.

15:56.623 --> 15:59.524
A couple of the shells fell off,
but...

16:02.662 --> 16:05.229
Just so that
you feel more at home.

16:06.533 --> 16:07.999
Thank you.

16:08.001 --> 16:10.001
I appreciate this.

16:15.275 --> 16:17.575
Is everything okay?

16:19.045 --> 16:21.746
That guy in the parking lot --
Who was he?

16:24.184 --> 16:26.184
Just one of my old friends.

16:26.186 --> 16:28.219
What happened?

16:30.557 --> 16:32.223
[ Sighs ]

16:32.225 --> 16:35.693
He just wrote some stuff
about me that he shouldn't have.

16:35.695 --> 16:38.162
TESS:
Is that why you're always sad?

16:38.598 --> 16:41.432
What?
Why do you care?

16:43.236 --> 16:45.403
Do you want some wine?

16:54.781 --> 16:56.647
[ Cellphone chimes ]

17:06.492 --> 17:09.460
Are you selling me out to Ray?

17:09.462 --> 17:11.229
Huh?

17:21.775 --> 17:24.175
- TESS: I'm leaving.
- You're what?

17:24.711 --> 17:27.578
I can't stay in Cebu
like this anymore.

17:27.579 --> 17:30.214
You're giving me nothing, and
they're willing to pay me big

17:30.216 --> 17:31.716
for some information on you.

17:33.520 --> 17:34.786
So you were just using me?

17:34.788 --> 17:36.654
<i>I</i> used <i> you?</i>

17:36.656 --> 17:39.590
You don't even know
when our anniversary is.

17:39.592 --> 17:41.626
The only time you ever call me
is when it's late at night,

17:41.628 --> 17:43.327
and you're wasted.

17:43.329 --> 17:45.363
You know, I thought that
you were gonna take me places

17:45.365 --> 17:48.332
and that you really loved me,
but no.

17:48.334 --> 17:50.201
You're not going anywhere.

17:50.203 --> 17:52.403
I <i> am</i> going somewhere!

17:52.405 --> 17:56.107
You're a pathetic loser
who's not good enough to go pro,

17:56.109 --> 17:59.811
and finding Mommy
isn't gonna help you.

18:00.513 --> 18:02.680
You wanna piss me off!

18:02.682 --> 18:03.781
Don't you?!

18:05.251 --> 18:06.851
What, are
you gonna kill me, too?

18:06.853 --> 18:08.586
What?

18:08.588 --> 18:11.222
You know
what I'm talking about --

18:11.224 --> 18:13.091
your brother.

18:20.400 --> 18:23.101
Get out!
Get out!

18:29.275 --> 18:31.576
[ Door slams ]

18:35.882 --> 18:37.782
[ Clatter ]

18:37.784 --> 18:40.118
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

19:10.216 --> 19:11.849
[ Tape recorder beeps ]

19:11.851 --> 19:14.185
BERRY: <i>You're the one
that stabbed him in the back.</i>

19:14.187 --> 19:15.920
<i>And for what?
For what?</i>

19:15.922 --> 19:18.256
<i>A headline and some cash?</i>

19:18.258 --> 19:20.158
[ Tape recorder beeps ]

19:20.160 --> 19:23.361
RICH: <i>You come around here
one more time, and you're done.</i>

19:23.363 --> 19:25.429
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

19:28.368 --> 19:30.568
- [ Cellphone beeps ]
- Hello?

19:30.570 --> 19:32.937
[ Crying ]
Ray, I need your help.

19:32.939 --> 19:35.606
It's Rich.

19:36.276 --> 19:38.576
He's lost his mind.

19:41.347 --> 19:43.581
[ Sobbing ]

19:43.583 --> 19:45.516
Thank you.

19:45.518 --> 19:46.751
Okay.

19:46.753 --> 19:49.253
Thank you so much.
[ Sniffles ]

19:51.758 --> 19:53.624
[ Cellphone beeps ]

19:56.563 --> 19:57.695
- [ Men grunt ]
- Good.

19:57.697 --> 19:58.796
Barnum, swim past him

19:58.798 --> 20:01.265
once you get him in position.

20:01.267 --> 20:03.334
Where the hell's Porter?

20:03.870 --> 20:06.204
Morning, Coach.

20:06.739 --> 20:09.407
Media Day was yesterday.

20:09.876 --> 20:12.944
For Rich's sake,
a little cooperation

20:12.946 --> 20:14.879
would be appreciated, sir.

20:14.881 --> 20:17.815
[ Indistinct shouting
in distance ]

20:17.817 --> 20:19.817
MAN: Move! Move!

20:23.890 --> 20:25.856
[ Knock on door ]

20:31.931 --> 20:33.998
Crap.
Look, I'm sorry.

20:34.000 --> 20:35.766
My alarm didn't go off.

20:38.738 --> 20:39.904
What?

20:51.484 --> 20:54.819
- I ne-- She set me up!
- Why?

20:54.821 --> 20:57.488
She's trying to fish money
out of Ray.

20:57.490 --> 20:59.357
What happened to your hand?

21:04.731 --> 21:06.764
[ Sighs ]

21:08.501 --> 21:10.501
- You were drinking, weren't you?
- No.

21:10.503 --> 21:12.336
Try again.
I can smell it on you.

21:12.338 --> 21:14.839
I didn't drink
until after we fought.

21:14.841 --> 21:17.408
[ Scoffs lightly ]
Okay.

21:17.410 --> 21:19.543
Let me get this straight.

21:19.979 --> 21:22.847
You got into an argument.
You broke up.

21:22.849 --> 21:24.949
You hit the wall.

21:24.951 --> 21:27.385
She hit her own face
to frame you.

21:27.387 --> 21:29.520
And then you got drunk?

21:30.423 --> 21:32.390
Hmm.

21:38.564 --> 21:40.965
Little trick I learned.

21:41.634 --> 21:45.403
I didn't see her hit herself.
She must have done it after.

21:46.439 --> 21:47.905
[ Sighs ]

21:47.907 --> 21:49.874
If she hasn't pressed charges
by now,

21:49.876 --> 21:52.009
that means she's probably
scheming something.

21:52.879 --> 21:54.712
You believe me, right?

21:55.481 --> 21:56.681
Yeah.

21:56.683 --> 21:58.783
Of course I do.

22:02.455 --> 22:04.021
You can be an idiot...

22:08.061 --> 22:10.628
...but you're not a monster.

22:13.833 --> 22:14.899
I got you a cell.

22:14.901 --> 22:16.867
Doesn't mean I'm gonna use it.

22:16.869 --> 22:18.969
That's fine,
'cause I'm only gonna call you

22:18.971 --> 22:21.772
when it's an emergency like
this one, and you better answer.

22:21.774 --> 22:23.908
- Yeah, we'll see.
- Hey!

22:23.910 --> 22:28.112
Remember who got you that
work visa and this apartment.

22:28.815 --> 22:32.717
I'm all you've got,
so don't piss me off.

22:34.754 --> 22:36.954
I know Miami called.

22:37.957 --> 22:39.390
You plan on going back?

22:39.392 --> 22:41.058
I made you a deal, didn't I?

22:41.060 --> 22:43.527
I intend on standing by that.

22:43.529 --> 22:44.995
Appreciate that.

22:44.997 --> 22:47.131
I play for you
until I find my mom.

22:47.133 --> 22:49.533
Then I'm done.

22:49.535 --> 22:50.701
Okay?

22:53.106 --> 22:55.139
Okay.

22:55.875 --> 22:57.641
Let's go.

22:57.643 --> 22:59.510
I don't want you
to be late for work.

23:02.014 --> 23:04.582
[ Slow music plays ]

23:06.552 --> 23:08.986
- RICH: Line up!
- Hey, you heard the man.

23:08.988 --> 23:12.456
Let's go! Line it up.
Let's run some routes.

23:13.059 --> 23:14.759
[ Sighs ]

23:14.761 --> 23:16.560
All right, guys.
Listen up.

23:16.562 --> 23:19.663
We're gonna run Tango Option 26.

23:20.099 --> 23:21.899
Go!

23:27.507 --> 23:28.472
Go!

23:31.711 --> 23:33.477
Come on, Coach!

23:33.479 --> 23:36.113
You plan on making this hard
at all on me today?

23:36.115 --> 23:38.616
Barnum, get out there
and give him some pressure.

23:38.618 --> 23:39.984
Lorne, get on the line
and block.

23:39.986 --> 23:41.519
Let's go!

23:46.125 --> 23:47.091
Go!

23:49.829 --> 23:50.961
Hey! Hey! Hey!

23:52.131 --> 23:53.631
MAN:
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

23:53.633 --> 23:55.699
- Hey, hey, hey, hey!
- Hey! Hey, that's enough!

23:55.701 --> 23:57.201
- That's enough.
- Easier hitting a woman?

23:57.203 --> 23:59.537
- I never touched her!
- Barnum, get off the field!

23:59.539 --> 24:00.738
You didn't think
I would have found out?

24:00.740 --> 24:02.640
I already told you.
I never...

24:02.642 --> 24:04.742
Hey.

24:08.047 --> 24:10.514
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

24:25.565 --> 24:28.032
[ Echoing ] Be strong.

24:28.034 --> 24:29.700
MAN: Mr. Porter?

24:29.702 --> 24:31.235
BRITTANY: Mr. Porter?

24:32.138 --> 24:34.071
Mr. Porter?

24:38.611 --> 24:39.777
What happened?

24:39.779 --> 24:41.111
Oh, you fainted during practice,

24:41.113 --> 24:43.080
and you blacked out for a while.

24:43.082 --> 24:44.815
Your coach sent you in.

24:45.785 --> 24:48.118
I'm Nurse Brittany Kim.

24:49.088 --> 24:51.622
What was the last thing
you remember?

24:53.259 --> 24:55.593
Getting hit hard.

24:56.963 --> 24:58.896
Do I have a concussion?

24:58.898 --> 25:00.898
Uh, well, we're not sure yet,

25:00.900 --> 25:05.202
but we're doing some scans
to check for brain trauma.

25:05.204 --> 25:07.805
[ Scoffs lightly ]
Really?

25:07.807 --> 25:10.107
I feel fine.

25:10.109 --> 25:12.643
Hey, Richard.
I'm Dr. Santiago.

25:12.645 --> 25:14.111
How are you feeling?

25:14.113 --> 25:16.947
Good.
I'm ready to get outta here.

25:16.949 --> 25:20.951
The reason you blacked out
was not because of a concussion.

25:20.953 --> 25:22.653
So then I don't need
to sit out long.

25:22.655 --> 25:25.155
You suffered a seizure
this morning.

25:25.157 --> 25:26.257
A seizure?

25:26.259 --> 25:28.659
You were out for nine hours.

25:28.661 --> 25:33.631
Have you been experiencing
headaches, memory loss, nausea?

25:33.633 --> 25:35.666
Get to the point.

25:36.869 --> 25:39.303
We found several lesions
in your brain.

25:39.305 --> 25:40.871
Lesions?

25:40.873 --> 25:43.140
DR. SANTIAGO:
Damaged tissue caused by tumors.

25:43.142 --> 25:44.875
So, what are you telling me?

25:44.877 --> 25:47.011
Are you saying
that I have a tumor?

25:47.013 --> 25:50.314
We believe you have a form
of glioblastoma multiforme.

25:50.316 --> 25:52.650
- It's a tumor in the brain.
- [ Loud ringing ]

25:52.652 --> 25:55.052
There's a number of treatments
and therapies

25:55.054 --> 25:58.689
that we can try first
to reduce the tumor.

25:58.691 --> 26:00.024
Permanent brain damage

26:00.026 --> 26:02.159
- or death can result.
- [ Ringing stops ]

26:06.999 --> 26:08.699
We know this is difficult
for you,

26:08.701 --> 26:11.802
but you need to get treatment
right away.

26:11.804 --> 26:14.004
Mr. Porter, we're not fi--

26:16.142 --> 26:18.943
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

26:27.053 --> 26:29.320
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

26:30.189 --> 26:32.056
Yeah? What is it?

26:34.193 --> 26:35.893
[ Lock disengages ]

26:36.862 --> 26:38.829
Rich!

26:42.201 --> 26:43.801
How'd you get the key?

26:43.803 --> 26:45.703
- I'm his landlord.
- [ Chuckles ]

26:45.705 --> 26:47.905
You might want
to keep the deposit.

26:47.907 --> 26:50.674
[ Sighs ] Lovely.

26:50.676 --> 26:53.844
- Rich!
- Rich!

26:59.385 --> 27:01.919
Any idea where he might be?

27:03.923 --> 27:06.090
[ Blues music plays ]

27:06.092 --> 27:08.626
[ Indistinct conversations ]

27:35.421 --> 27:37.721
Where are you?

27:39.959 --> 27:42.760
I need you to go back
to the hospital.

27:46.332 --> 27:48.165
I made all the arrangements.

27:48.167 --> 27:49.967
It's one of the best hospitals
in the country.

27:49.969 --> 27:51.902
You have nothing to worry about.

27:52.772 --> 27:55.406
The league would have caught
this early during the physical.

27:55.408 --> 27:57.708
Okay, look, we're taking you
back to the hospital,

27:57.710 --> 27:59.877
and you're gonna stay there.
Don't worry.

27:59.879 --> 28:02.212
We'll clean up your place
and move all your things.

28:02.214 --> 28:03.847
- I'm not giving up on her.
- No one's saying

28:03.849 --> 28:05.883
you should give up on her.

28:06.719 --> 28:07.851
I'll take these.

28:08.387 --> 28:09.987
You make phone calls
on the other half.

28:09.989 --> 28:12.022
And if you find something,
let me know,

28:12.024 --> 28:13.724
and I will check it out.

28:26.138 --> 28:28.472
We're in this, too.

28:30.710 --> 28:33.043
- I got to pack.
- We'll help.

28:33.045 --> 28:34.278
We're all outside.

28:34.280 --> 28:36.447
Why do you keep saying "we"?

29:19.892 --> 29:22.092
[ Engine starts in distance ]

29:24.997 --> 29:27.164
[ Engine starts ]

29:29.468 --> 29:32.803
[ Breathes deeply ]

29:37.143 --> 29:39.143
SAMMY: Mama.

29:42.314 --> 29:44.381
It's nothing.

29:52.358 --> 29:53.390
Mnh-mnh.

29:53.392 --> 29:56.226
Mama, what happened?

30:18.584 --> 30:20.984
This is your room.

30:26.192 --> 30:28.225
It's small.

30:29.495 --> 30:32.062
- So, I have to stay here?
- Yes.

30:32.064 --> 30:35.199
We are quite far from the city,
and treatments are frequent.

30:35.201 --> 30:37.401
Plus, we can't risk
you being alone again

30:37.403 --> 30:39.503
if you have another seizure.

30:43.142 --> 30:45.275
Wait. Do I share a room
with someone?

30:45.277 --> 30:48.011
Yeah. We are undergoing
lots of renovations right now,

30:48.013 --> 30:49.980
so there are
no single rooms available.

30:50.516 --> 30:53.550
Visiting hours will be
from 8:00 a.m. to 9:00 p.m.

31:00.492 --> 31:03.026
Is this you?

31:05.397 --> 31:07.564
Kid, do you speak English?

31:09.268 --> 31:10.934
What, is he deaf, too?

31:11.604 --> 31:14.504
Mr. Porter, this is Darrell.

31:14.506 --> 31:17.407
I believe you two are teammates.

31:22.648 --> 31:24.581
I have to room with a kid?

31:24.583 --> 31:28.118
Yes. The children's ward
is shut down,

31:28.120 --> 31:30.254
and we are pairing patients
with GBM.

31:30.256 --> 31:31.588
Also, your coach thought

31:31.590 --> 31:33.657
- that since --
- No, you don't understand.

31:33.659 --> 31:35.993
I'm not rooming with a kid!

31:36.962 --> 31:38.428
BRITTANY:
Can you keep your voice down?

31:38.430 --> 31:40.430
My time and patience
is growing thin with you,

31:40.432 --> 31:42.933
so I will be frank.

31:42.935 --> 31:45.669
This is your room, you are
to be paired with Darrell,

31:45.671 --> 31:47.638
and you are to stay here
at all times.

31:47.640 --> 31:49.239
Don't leave
without my permission.

31:49.241 --> 31:52.376
And don't ever yell at me again.

31:52.378 --> 31:54.678
You understand?

31:54.680 --> 31:57.381
- Mm-hmm.
- Mm.

31:57.383 --> 31:58.982
All right.

31:58.984 --> 32:01.919
Make yourself at home.
Treatment starts at 3:00.

32:09.628 --> 32:12.229
There's not even any TV.

32:13.632 --> 32:16.266
Yep.
I'm gonna die.

32:18.103 --> 32:20.470
I got to run some errands,
so do me a favor

32:20.472 --> 32:24.508
and just don't tell
Nurse Ratched.

32:27.079 --> 32:29.046
What? Oh.

32:29.048 --> 32:32.182
Yeah... you too.

32:35.020 --> 32:36.386
Uh, can you take me here?

32:36.388 --> 32:38.588
St. Matthew's Orphanage.

32:43.495 --> 32:45.629
[ Engine starts ]

32:45.631 --> 32:47.965
Just wait here, okay?

33:10.089 --> 33:12.622
Thank you.

33:21.700 --> 33:23.600
[ Clock clicking ]

33:43.188 --> 33:46.056
[ Children shouting playfully,
child laughing ]

33:46.658 --> 33:50.794
Well, I do remember her,
but she doesn't work for us.

33:51.430 --> 33:54.798
She worked as a missionary
that helped the orphanage.

33:54.800 --> 33:58.301
She would only come by
from time to time.

33:58.303 --> 34:00.237
Do you have an address?

34:00.239 --> 34:02.472
She was with a mission group
from the States,

34:02.474 --> 34:06.143
but I'm not sure
where she took residency.

34:10.716 --> 34:15.118
These children are going through
the hardest time of their lives.

34:15.120 --> 34:19.222
They're learning at a young age
on what it's like to have faith.

34:19.224 --> 34:21.658
They will all go far.

34:24.763 --> 34:26.496
My mom did all this?

34:26.498 --> 34:28.532
From what I recall,

34:28.534 --> 34:31.268
she was one of the best at it.

34:31.270 --> 34:35.105
She was really creative on how
to connect with the children.

34:38.677 --> 34:42.579
I'm sorry
I couldn't be of more service.

34:43.248 --> 34:44.514
That's okay.

34:44.516 --> 34:46.149
Thank you for your help.

34:46.150 --> 34:48.552
- God bless.
- Thanks.

34:51.857 --> 34:54.391
[ Slow music plays ]

35:04.636 --> 35:07.270
[ Speaking native language ]

35:11.610 --> 35:13.376
[ Rich coughing ]

35:25.691 --> 35:27.557
Let me see.

35:34.299 --> 35:36.700
These old tires
aren't sitting right...

35:36.702 --> 35:38.602
rubbing.

35:40.606 --> 35:42.873
It might need a new paint job.

35:42.875 --> 35:45.509
Checking it out.

35:46.879 --> 35:49.179
Thank you.

35:49.681 --> 35:51.815
You speak English?

35:52.751 --> 35:57.187
[ Breathes deeply ]

35:57.189 --> 35:59.222
About those things
that I said...

35:59.224 --> 36:01.558
I forgive you.

36:06.532 --> 36:08.598
Don't be afraid.

36:09.434 --> 36:10.667
Of what?

36:10.669 --> 36:12.602
This?

36:13.305 --> 36:14.404
I'm not.

36:16.375 --> 36:18.308
Why are you shaking?

36:22.381 --> 36:24.648
Do you want to play a game
with me?

36:35.861 --> 36:37.227
I remember this game.

36:37.229 --> 36:39.663
Electronic football?

36:39.665 --> 36:41.598
Does this thing even work?

36:41.600 --> 36:44.601
DARRELL: No.
Something new.

36:46.772 --> 36:48.772
RICH: What is this?

36:48.774 --> 36:50.540
"'The 100 Yards of Life.'

36:50.542 --> 36:53.877
The magical game that can heal."
[ Scoffs ]

37:02.688 --> 37:03.954
"10-yard pass.

37:03.956 --> 37:06.289
To move forward 10 yards,
try a new dish

37:06.291 --> 37:08.558
that you've never had before.

37:08.560 --> 37:10.660
Time limit is three days.

37:10.662 --> 37:12.996
If you don't do this task
in the given time limit,

37:12.998 --> 37:17.267
you receive a penalty, and
you must move back 10 yards."

37:17.636 --> 37:19.936
[ Sighs ]

37:19.938 --> 37:21.538
You should try balut.

37:21.540 --> 37:22.906
It's high in protein.

37:22.908 --> 37:24.641
Uh, you know what?

37:24.643 --> 37:27.544
I think I'll try to find
something new in the cafeteria.

37:33.318 --> 37:35.318
"10-yard power run.

37:35.320 --> 37:38.588
Join a support group
and make new friends."

37:40.425 --> 37:41.925
RICH: Hey.
What are you doing?

37:41.927 --> 37:44.561
I joined the Cebu Saints.

37:45.764 --> 37:47.631
Okay.

37:53.272 --> 37:55.038
"No-huddle play.

37:55.040 --> 37:56.840
Give up a bad habit.

37:56.842 --> 37:59.909
Every week you give up a bad
habit, you move up 5 yards.

37:59.911 --> 38:04.047
Every time you do the bad habit
is a 5-yard penalty."

38:04.883 --> 38:06.783
You getting it?

38:07.919 --> 38:09.619
Got it.

38:13.859 --> 38:17.460
So, this game
really heals people, huh?

38:17.462 --> 38:18.595
It has.

38:19.898 --> 38:22.299
- Do you like it?
- Yeah.

38:22.301 --> 38:24.401
It's gonna be fun.

38:26.071 --> 38:29.606
Hey, why the Bible verses
on the back of the cards?

38:29.608 --> 38:31.074
Because it's by God.

38:31.076 --> 38:34.010
It's how the magic works.

38:35.480 --> 38:37.080
Hmm.

38:37.082 --> 38:39.849
[ Loud ringing ]

38:44.790 --> 38:47.557
[ Ringing continues ]

38:55.734 --> 38:58.034
[ Grunts ]

39:09.348 --> 39:10.947
What are you doing?

39:12.718 --> 39:15.618
I always pray for my patients.

39:18.123 --> 39:20.957
You had a seizure again,
causing you to black out.

39:21.860 --> 39:23.893
How are you feeling?

39:25.430 --> 39:28.365
Like I fell and hit my head
on the toilet.

39:34.039 --> 39:35.872
[ Groans ]

39:39.077 --> 39:42.379
Well, Darrell
brought you breakfast.

39:42.381 --> 39:45.582
Mm. Thank you.

39:46.985 --> 39:50.854
- He said you wanted to try it.
- It's balut.

39:50.856 --> 39:52.722
What did I tell you?

39:52.724 --> 39:54.791
It's from the cafeteria,

39:54.793 --> 39:56.993
like what you said.

39:57.963 --> 39:59.596
They make this at the cafeteria?

40:01.066 --> 40:03.166
Well, it's protein-rich.

40:03.168 --> 40:06.536
And you should have it
while it's hot.

40:08.039 --> 40:09.906
All right.

40:11.510 --> 40:12.842
How do I...

40:12.844 --> 40:14.477
[ Darrell laughs ]

40:15.981 --> 40:17.514
I don't know what I'm doing.

40:21.887 --> 40:24.487
BRITTANY:
Duck embryo, one week old,

40:24.489 --> 40:26.923
feathers and bones
partially formed.

40:26.925 --> 40:28.591
Enjoy.

40:33.665 --> 40:36.533
One important thing.

40:36.535 --> 40:38.101
What is this?

40:38.103 --> 40:40.069
Salt.

40:40.071 --> 40:42.205
Salt.

40:43.675 --> 40:45.909
Here's to "100 Yards."

40:49.080 --> 40:51.514
[ Crunching ]

40:52.684 --> 40:54.517
[ Groans ]

40:57.656 --> 40:59.122
BRITTANY: [ Chuckles ]

41:01.626 --> 41:04.727
All right, so, you have three
more to check, and I have four.

41:04.729 --> 41:07.497
No.
I have <i> seven</i> more to check.

41:07.499 --> 41:09.165
You have four more
to make calls on.

41:09.167 --> 41:12.469
Rich, stay in the hospital.
I mean it.

41:12.471 --> 41:15.238
I can't sit here while I need
to be looking for her!

41:15.240 --> 41:17.874
- Rich, hey, calm down.
- RICH: I'm losing my mind.

41:17.876 --> 41:20.610
Listen to me.
I got this, okay?

41:20.612 --> 41:23.179
Just find something to do at the
hospital to keep yourself busy.

41:23.181 --> 41:25.148
We will find her.

41:25.150 --> 41:26.916
I promise.

41:27.652 --> 41:28.651
[ Cellphone beeps ]

41:28.653 --> 41:30.253
[ Dial tone ]

41:37.596 --> 41:39.729
Do you wanna play with me?

41:40.799 --> 41:42.799
Do you have anything else
that we can play?

41:44.135 --> 41:45.568
[ Beeping ]

41:45.570 --> 41:47.170
Oh, yeah.

41:49.074 --> 41:50.707
[ Beeping ]

41:53.745 --> 41:55.111
[ Gasps ]

41:55.113 --> 41:57.046
[ Beeping continues ]

42:05.957 --> 42:07.657
Okay.

42:07.659 --> 42:11.060
Tess, let me just start
by apologizing in advance.

42:11.062 --> 42:13.696
I know this isn't easy.

42:13.698 --> 42:16.232
I'm sure you understand
that we just need more details

42:16.234 --> 42:18.968
before we can move
on something like this.

42:19.804 --> 42:21.070
Okay.

42:21.072 --> 42:22.972
All right.

42:22.974 --> 42:25.241
[ Tape recorder beeping ]

42:25.944 --> 42:27.710
Okay.

42:27.712 --> 42:29.112
Let's, uh...

42:30.549 --> 42:31.881
Okay, let's start with --

42:31.883 --> 42:36.252
And, please,
as many details as possible.

42:38.290 --> 42:40.890
When you were attacked,
how did you get away?

42:41.760 --> 42:43.726
Um...

42:44.896 --> 42:47.564
He finally just, uh...

42:47.999 --> 42:50.300
He got tired and let me go.

42:52.671 --> 42:55.004
But you said you escaped, right?

42:55.006 --> 42:56.739
I did.
I clawed at him.

42:56.741 --> 42:59.943
And he got tired and fell over.

42:59.945 --> 43:02.979
But you realize
Rich had no scratches on him?

43:07.018 --> 43:09.218
I don't remember.

43:11.356 --> 43:13.990
I'm trying to block it out.

43:16.127 --> 43:19.128
And tell me again -- Why did
you not go to the police?

43:19.130 --> 43:21.798
Because I was scared.

43:22.233 --> 43:24.934
You can't trust anyone here.

43:28.673 --> 43:31.374
Tess, do you remember
packing your clothes?

43:31.376 --> 43:33.710
- What are you talking about?
- When you saw me,

43:33.712 --> 43:35.712
you had a bag
filled with your clothes.

43:35.714 --> 43:37.847
I'm just trying to put it
together in my head.

43:37.849 --> 43:40.116
How did you have time
to pack your clothes

43:40.118 --> 43:42.051
if you were struggling
for your life, trying to escape?

43:42.053 --> 43:43.353
- How did...
- [ Tape recorder beeps ]

43:44.823 --> 43:47.357
What the hell are you doing?

43:47.359 --> 43:50.393
You said you wanted a story.

43:51.129 --> 43:53.029
"The bigger the story,
the bigger the pay" --

43:53.031 --> 43:55.398
That's what you said to me.

43:56.301 --> 43:58.134
No.

43:59.938 --> 44:03.039
- What have you done, Tess?
- TESS: What do you care?

44:03.041 --> 44:05.908
You had no hesitation writing
the story about his brother,

44:05.910 --> 44:07.744
and now you want one on me.

44:07.746 --> 44:11.014
Do you really think that
Rich is gonna be your friend

44:11.016 --> 44:14.417
- after all of this?
- I need you to leave.

44:17.789 --> 44:19.922
You know, there are
plenty of other reporters

44:19.924 --> 44:21.224
who are willing to pay
for the full story.

44:21.226 --> 44:22.392
The door.

44:37.976 --> 44:39.442
[ Elevator bell dings ]

45:41.306 --> 45:43.740
So, you're treating Rich Porter?

45:43.742 --> 45:45.842
Yeah.
He's a handful.

45:45.844 --> 45:48.044
He has a temper,
from what I hear.

45:48.046 --> 45:51.748
Yeah, but I try my best
to be patient with him.

45:53.351 --> 45:55.418
I do see a lot of pain in him,
though.

45:55.420 --> 45:57.854
Like Dom?

45:58.456 --> 46:00.289
Yeah.

46:00.291 --> 46:02.959
Scary how much
he reminds me of Dom.

46:02.961 --> 46:04.827
Be careful.

46:04.829 --> 46:06.329
Of?

46:06.331 --> 46:08.231
Getting too involved with him.

46:08.233 --> 46:10.900
It's not how
you're gonna find your peace.

46:13.104 --> 46:15.905
I know he's not Dom.

46:15.907 --> 46:19.942
I'm just doing my job,
and I won't give up on him.

46:19.944 --> 46:21.778
- Okay?
- Okay.

46:21.780 --> 46:23.446
Okay.

46:24.115 --> 46:25.882
[ Pager beeps ]

46:27.519 --> 46:29.185
There you go.

46:29.187 --> 46:31.821
- Thank you.
- [ Beeping continues ]

46:34.058 --> 46:35.792
[ Beeping continues ]

46:38.863 --> 46:40.429
What'd you do with them?

46:40.431 --> 46:42.431
You're not allowed to be
drinking during treatment.

46:42.433 --> 46:44.267
You're not allowed
to go through my things.

46:44.269 --> 46:45.868
I need it to sleep.

46:45.870 --> 46:47.403
That's an excuse.

46:47.405 --> 46:49.872
We have many other methods
to help you with sleep.

46:49.874 --> 46:52.909
That's no excuse
to go through my stuff.

46:53.545 --> 46:56.512
Is this what you do
with your fiancÃ©?

46:56.514 --> 46:57.513
Hmm?

46:57.515 --> 47:00.283
Go through his things?

47:00.285 --> 47:02.251
See if he's messing around?

47:04.556 --> 47:07.156
Don't talk about him again.

47:08.593 --> 47:11.460
Go ahead and drink all you want.

47:22.173 --> 47:24.006
[ Tires screeching ]

47:30.448 --> 47:32.615
[ Clock ticking ]

47:32.617 --> 47:35.084
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

47:38.156 --> 47:39.589
[ Cellphone beeps ]

47:40.992 --> 47:43.059
BRITTANY: Hello?

47:45.263 --> 47:47.363
Okay.
I'll be right there.

47:47.365 --> 47:49.098
[ Cellphone beeps ]

47:50.268 --> 47:53.336
[ Up-tempo music plays,
indistinct shouting ]

47:54.439 --> 47:55.905
Hey!

47:55.907 --> 47:58.541
It's okay.
I got him.

47:58.543 --> 48:00.610
I got him.

48:01.279 --> 48:04.213
So, oh, you're so handsome.

48:04.215 --> 48:05.982
Where are you staying?

48:05.984 --> 48:08.050
- No.
- Huh? "No" what?

48:08.052 --> 48:11.087
Come on.
"No" what?

48:12.123 --> 48:15.191
- No, Tess.
- [ Laughs ] Tess?

48:15.193 --> 48:17.159
Come on.
Where you staying, huh?

48:17.161 --> 48:19.462
Where you staying, huh?

48:19.464 --> 48:21.931
Aah! Oh!

48:21.933 --> 48:24.433
- Aah!
- [ Coughing ]

48:24.435 --> 48:27.036
- Hey!
- What?!

48:27.038 --> 48:28.604
Thanks for letting me
borrow your phone.

48:30.642 --> 48:32.441
[ Groans ]

48:44.022 --> 48:46.055
[ Engine shuts off ]

48:50.461 --> 48:52.628
BRITTANY: Rich?

48:52.630 --> 48:54.263
Rich?

48:54.265 --> 48:56.198
- Hey.
- Hey.

48:56.200 --> 48:59.101
- Get in the car.
- Hey.

48:59.103 --> 49:00.536
I tried to drink myself
to death,

49:00.538 --> 49:02.939
but I didn't have enough cash.

49:02.941 --> 49:05.007
Wait.
Do you have about 10 bucks?

49:05.009 --> 49:06.175
That should about do it.

49:06.177 --> 49:08.044
Let's go.

49:09.447 --> 49:11.080
- RICH: No. No.
- [ Vehicle door opens ]

49:11.082 --> 49:12.281
BRITTANY: All right.
Get in.

49:12.283 --> 49:14.216
RICH: Ow!

49:14.953 --> 49:16.452
[ Vehicle door closes ]

49:31.202 --> 49:32.702
[ Engine shuts off ]

49:34.639 --> 49:36.605
We're here.

49:41.379 --> 49:42.411
Thank you.

49:45.249 --> 49:47.083
[ Clears throat ]

49:47.085 --> 49:50.119
No more.
You understand?

49:50.555 --> 49:52.121
If you leave one more time --

49:52.123 --> 49:55.224
I really do need to start
playing the piano again.

50:03.401 --> 50:06.635
Your mum taught you
to play the piano?

50:08.639 --> 50:10.039
Yeah.

50:10.041 --> 50:12.074
I was really good.

50:13.344 --> 50:18.080
And when Logan was born,
I wrote him a song.

50:18.082 --> 50:19.348
I called it "Logan's Song."

50:19.350 --> 50:21.350
She loved it.

50:22.186 --> 50:24.487
So, where's Logan now?

50:28.159 --> 50:30.192
He's dead.

50:34.298 --> 50:36.298
I'm sorry.

50:42.306 --> 50:44.240
What happened?

50:46.677 --> 50:49.478
RICH:
We were on our way home.

50:52.183 --> 50:55.384
He had this, uh, model car.

50:55.820 --> 50:58.487
Something that we'd both
built together.

50:58.489 --> 51:01.557
I wasn't really paying attention
to him much.

51:03.261 --> 51:08.531
I was getting text after text
from friends and girls.

51:10.635 --> 51:13.436
Kept trying to talk to me.

51:13.438 --> 51:14.737
[ No audio ]

51:14.739 --> 51:16.605
And I kept just putting him off.

51:24.215 --> 51:27.149
I eventually put my phone down

51:27.151 --> 51:29.351
to listen
to what he was saying to me.

51:32.156 --> 51:36.759
And he was talking to me
about how I was his hero.

51:41.666 --> 51:44.166
And I looked over, and I smiled.

51:49.340 --> 51:52.374
It was the last thing
I ever heard him say.

51:52.376 --> 51:54.577
Not a moment later,
I hear him scream.

51:54.579 --> 51:57.113
- [ Logan screaming ]
- And I look up,

51:57.115 --> 51:58.747
and there's an animal
in the road.

51:58.749 --> 52:01.183
[ Tires screeching ]

52:01.185 --> 52:04.753
All I could see
was trees and glass and...

52:05.823 --> 52:08.157
- ...dirt.
- [ Tires screeching ]

52:08.159 --> 52:09.758
[ Crash ]

52:11.529 --> 52:15.164
I looked around to see if...

52:15.166 --> 52:17.867
if Logan was still in his chair.

52:22.907 --> 52:24.206
And I saw him.

52:32.483 --> 52:35.184
I got him, and I wrapped him up.

52:37.455 --> 52:39.622
And he was cold.

52:40.825 --> 52:43.826
And he -- he was cold
because he just...

52:43.828 --> 52:46.262
he wasn't there anymore.

52:48.399 --> 52:51.200
[ Voice breaking ]
They said it wasn't my fault.

52:51.636 --> 52:53.869
But I know
that if I was paying attention,

52:53.871 --> 52:56.505
none of this
would have happened.

52:58.843 --> 53:01.510
I killed my family.

53:01.946 --> 53:03.913
And now I'm gonna die.

53:03.915 --> 53:06.515
You're not going to die.

53:08.886 --> 53:10.886
- Think about your mum. She --
- They're gone.

53:10.888 --> 53:14.757
All of them are gone,
and I'm to blame.

53:16.561 --> 53:17.893
I'm scared.
I don't --

53:17.895 --> 53:20.496
I don't know
what I'm supposed to do anymore,

53:20.498 --> 53:21.830
and I'm scared,
and I don't...

53:21.832 --> 53:23.632
[ Crying ]

53:25.970 --> 53:28.237
It's okay.

53:30.875 --> 53:32.942
It's okay.

53:38.716 --> 53:41.684
- Rich.
- [ Sighs ]

53:42.453 --> 53:43.652
I'm sorry.

53:43.654 --> 53:46.355
I shouldn't have done that.
I...

53:46.357 --> 53:48.257
Sorry.

53:52.396 --> 53:54.763
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

54:07.778 --> 54:09.979
[ Breathes deeply ]

54:19.724 --> 54:22.258
[ Clatter ]

54:35.506 --> 54:36.805
[ Door disengages ]

54:39.710 --> 54:40.943
Juan?

54:45.316 --> 54:48.817
[ Door closes ]

54:48.819 --> 54:51.587
Hi, Mommy.

54:51.589 --> 54:53.822
Bring this to the kitchen.

55:16.480 --> 55:19.848
But I don't need you
to watch me, too.

55:30.861 --> 55:33.829
- [ Door opens ]
- [ Crying ]

55:33.831 --> 55:35.831
[ Door closes ]

56:20.978 --> 56:23.979
[ Coughs ]

56:33.824 --> 56:35.924
[ Sighs ]

56:57.047 --> 56:59.114
[ Razor buzzing ]

57:10.628 --> 57:12.694
- Rich.
- Look, about last night...

57:12.696 --> 57:14.463
- No.
- ...I was...

57:14.465 --> 57:15.731
Look.

57:15.733 --> 57:18.600
I didn't do any of these things.

57:19.470 --> 57:21.804
It's a gossip magazine.
It's not even credible news.

57:21.806 --> 57:24.473
Yeah, but it's still
really serious,

57:24.475 --> 57:26.642
which is why I need to make sure
that you don't go in the city,

57:26.644 --> 57:28.944
- at least for now.
- Why?

57:28.946 --> 57:31.780
You think --
You think I did this?

57:31.782 --> 57:33.782
Of course not.

57:33.784 --> 57:35.717
- Good.
- [ Pager beeps ]

57:37.721 --> 57:38.887
Okay, I'll be right back.

57:38.889 --> 57:41.156
- Okay?
- Okay.

57:41.792 --> 57:43.959
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

57:58.209 --> 57:59.508
Rich Porter?

58:00.878 --> 58:02.711
- Hey, we're talking to you.
- I don't want any trouble.

58:02.713 --> 58:06.181
Hey! You think you can come here
and abuse my sister, huh?

58:06.183 --> 58:07.549
- She's a liar.
- [ Grunts ]

58:11.188 --> 58:14.556
Take that!
Dumb thug!

58:21.632 --> 58:22.865
[ Tires screech ]

58:27.538 --> 58:28.637
Where's the knife?

58:28.638 --> 58:29.737
Hold it! Get Rich out of here --
now! Let's go!

58:29.740 --> 58:31.507
I'll take care of this.
Just go.

58:31.509 --> 58:33.208
Get out of here.
I'll cover you. Go, go, go.

58:33.210 --> 58:35.244
- [ Indistinct shouting ]
- Hurry, hurry. Get in the car.

58:35.246 --> 58:37.145
Hey. How you doing?
Hey. How are you?

58:43.988 --> 58:45.521
RAY: She's a con.

58:46.790 --> 58:48.056
She's a con.

58:48.058 --> 58:50.025
She fabricated everything.

58:50.027 --> 58:51.727
MAN:
She was your source.

58:51.729 --> 58:53.262
What the hell's going on?

58:53.264 --> 58:56.598
She was playing Porter
the whole time.

58:56.600 --> 58:58.600
And now she's playing me
against him.

58:58.602 --> 59:00.536
MAN: We know
you wanted the story, Ray,

59:00.538 --> 59:02.838
but we didn't send you there
because you said you needed it.

59:02.840 --> 59:05.607
We sent you there because
you said you would write a story

59:05.609 --> 59:08.076
that would fix his image
for the league.

59:08.078 --> 59:10.612
Now it's blowing up
in our faces.

59:10.614 --> 59:12.848
The story's not over.

59:14.885 --> 59:17.019
Just give me a week.

59:17.021 --> 59:19.888
Give me a week,
and I'll get you what you need.

59:21.592 --> 59:23.659
What's up, dude?

59:24.094 --> 59:25.861
- How's the water?
- Good.

59:25.863 --> 59:28.864
Nice. All right.

59:32.136 --> 59:34.703
I need to know who you are.

59:35.239 --> 59:38.240
Just a dying man
trying to figure things out.

59:39.577 --> 59:41.910
And a man
who's hiding something.

59:43.247 --> 59:47.282
I lost contact with my mom
a little over a year ago.

59:47.284 --> 59:49.084
She went missing.

59:49.086 --> 59:51.587
And I know
that she's here somewhere.

59:52.022 --> 59:54.590
That's the reason why I'm here.

59:55.125 --> 59:57.092
I'm not running from anybody
or anything.

59:57.995 --> 01:00:01.163
She's the only thing
that I care about.

01:00:01.165 --> 01:00:04.032
Did you do those things
to that woman?

01:00:04.034 --> 01:00:06.001
No.
I promise you.

01:00:06.003 --> 01:00:08.303
She's just trying
to get a payday.

01:00:11.075 --> 01:00:13.175
How can I believe you?

01:00:13.177 --> 01:00:15.811
[ Water splashing ]

01:00:15.813 --> 01:00:17.312
He's having a seizure!

01:00:17.314 --> 01:00:19.081
Darrell! Darrell!

01:00:21.352 --> 01:00:24.052
Stay with me.
Help! Help!

01:00:24.054 --> 01:00:26.288
Buddy, stay with me.
Stay with me.

01:00:26.290 --> 01:00:28.857
He's having a seizure!

01:00:30.361 --> 01:00:32.828
- Why is he doing this?
- It's all right. It's okay.

01:00:32.830 --> 01:00:35.130
- Why is he still...
- Come on. Let's go.

01:00:35.132 --> 01:00:36.298
- Darrell!
- We've got him, all right?

01:00:36.300 --> 01:00:38.300
It's gonna be okay.

01:00:48.112 --> 01:00:49.711
Does it hurt?

01:00:49.713 --> 01:00:51.013
It does now.

01:00:51.015 --> 01:00:52.881
I didn't even notice it before.

01:00:54.652 --> 01:00:56.752
Look...

01:00:56.754 --> 01:00:59.287
about last night, I'm sorry.

01:01:00.024 --> 01:01:02.758
It's okay.
You weren't yourself.

01:01:06.897 --> 01:01:08.230
Earlier, those men...

01:01:08.232 --> 01:01:10.365
The police got one of them.

01:01:10.367 --> 01:01:12.300
And the other --
They're still searching.

01:01:12.302 --> 01:01:13.969
But don't worry.

01:01:13.971 --> 01:01:16.004
They'll get him.

01:01:20.310 --> 01:01:24.279
When the knife came at me,
I thought that's how it ended.

01:01:25.249 --> 01:01:29.117
All I could think about
was leaving everybody behind.

01:01:29.753 --> 01:01:32.721
Coach, team, Darrell...

01:01:33.724 --> 01:01:35.424
...and you.

01:01:36.827 --> 01:01:39.094
And that terrified me.

01:01:42.700 --> 01:01:44.232
- It's okay.
- I was so scared.

01:01:44.234 --> 01:01:46.802
- It's okay.
- [ Crying ]

01:01:50.908 --> 01:01:52.274
How is he?

01:01:52.276 --> 01:01:53.475
- He's fine...
- Is he okay?

01:01:53.477 --> 01:01:55.744
...thanks to you.

01:01:56.246 --> 01:01:59.281
Let's go see him.

01:02:03.320 --> 01:02:06.922
[ Up-tempo music plays ]

01:02:06.924 --> 01:02:08.757
With two minutes remaining,
Papua New Guinea

01:02:08.759 --> 01:02:11.827
is rushing down the field
for another touchdown.

01:02:11.829 --> 01:02:14.129
- [ Indistinct shouting ]
- We need to stop them.

01:02:14.131 --> 01:02:16.264
Yeah, we got to stop them
on the third down.

01:02:16.266 --> 01:02:18.767
Otherwise, Papua New Guinea
is gonna run the clock.

01:02:18.769 --> 01:02:20.902
MAN: Break.

01:02:22.339 --> 01:02:23.271
Move!

01:02:26.376 --> 01:02:28.143
- Hike!
- [ Indistinct shouting ]

01:02:31.181 --> 01:02:34.116
- [ Whistle blows ]
- That's it, baby! That's it!

01:02:34.118 --> 01:02:36.885
[ Cheers and applause ]

01:02:39.323 --> 01:02:40.956
- Yeah!
- ANNOUNCER: Kelly Barnum

01:02:40.958 --> 01:02:43.992
has recovered the fumble,
and it's Saints' ball.

01:02:47.965 --> 01:02:49.164
[ Sighs ]

01:02:49.166 --> 01:02:50.432
Hey, how you doing
with the game?

01:02:50.434 --> 01:02:51.900
I have to finish my painting

01:02:51.902 --> 01:02:53.935
and make the first step
to my dream job.

01:02:53.937 --> 01:02:55.337
What's that?

01:02:55.339 --> 01:02:57.539
- To be a quarterback like you.
- [ Chuckles ]

01:02:57.541 --> 01:03:00.142
You know, I can teach you how
to throw a spiral, if you want.

01:03:00.144 --> 01:03:02.377
- What was your next card?
- Um...

01:03:02.379 --> 01:03:06.815
go out on a date with a special
someone or with a new crush.

01:03:06.817 --> 01:03:09.818
I have to pair up two friends
for one of my cards.

01:03:09.820 --> 01:03:12.954
- Maybe we can help each other.
- Yeah, yeah.

01:03:12.956 --> 01:03:15.323
Let's look for someone
we can ask out here tonight.

01:03:17.094 --> 01:03:18.326
- Uh...
- Hey, lady!

01:03:18.328 --> 01:03:20.462
Want to go out with Rich Porter?

01:03:20.464 --> 01:03:21.897
[ Woman chuckles ]

01:03:21.899 --> 01:03:24.166
Don't worry.
We'll do that later, bud.

01:03:24.168 --> 01:03:26.268
Anyways, Coach has me set up
with a meeting

01:03:26.270 --> 01:03:30.038
with a sports agent tonight
for when we recover.

01:03:30.040 --> 01:03:32.007
Maybe I'll put in a good word
for you.

01:03:32.009 --> 01:03:33.208
Tell him that you're
an up-and-comer.

01:03:33.210 --> 01:03:35.844
Yeah? All right.

01:03:35.846 --> 01:03:37.946
ANNOUNCER: And the Saints
offense takes the field

01:03:37.948 --> 01:03:39.948
with less than a minute
remaining.

01:03:39.950 --> 01:03:42.384
Right.
All right, let's watch us win.

01:03:42.386 --> 01:03:44.052
MAN: Hut!

01:03:46.023 --> 01:03:47.823
[ Whistle blows ]

01:03:47.825 --> 01:03:48.957
DENISE: Oh!

01:03:48.959 --> 01:03:50.525
[ Cheers and applause ]

01:03:50.527 --> 01:03:52.093
[ Groans ]

01:03:52.095 --> 01:03:53.461
Come on, Miah!

01:03:55.165 --> 01:03:57.866
- Come on! You got this!
- [ Grunts ]

01:03:57.868 --> 01:03:59.501
I can't handle the pressure,
guys.

01:03:59.503 --> 01:04:01.469
- I can't.
- We got this, bro.

01:04:01.471 --> 01:04:02.971
- Focus.
- That guy!

01:04:02.973 --> 01:04:04.105
That guy over there.

01:04:04.107 --> 01:04:05.340
I'm gonna kill you!

01:04:05.342 --> 01:04:06.908
Where's the ball?
Ha!

01:04:06.910 --> 01:04:08.243
Have faith in yourself, bro.

01:04:08.245 --> 01:04:10.946
- Come on.
- Yeah, yeah.

01:04:11.481 --> 01:04:14.282
All right.
Let's win this thing, yeah?

01:04:14.284 --> 01:04:15.951
- Yeah, yeah.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

01:04:15.953 --> 01:04:17.219
- You want that slant?
- Yes!

01:04:17.221 --> 01:04:19.254
It's yours.

01:04:19.256 --> 01:04:22.123
- Option 29, slant and go.
- Okay.

01:04:22.125 --> 01:04:23.425
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

01:04:23.427 --> 01:04:25.894
All right.
"Saints" on 3.

01:04:25.896 --> 01:04:28.597
- 1, 2, 3.
- TOGETHER: Saints!

01:04:36.907 --> 01:04:39.474
ANNOUNCER: This will be
the last play of the game.

01:04:39.476 --> 01:04:40.909
Hike!

01:04:43.947 --> 01:04:45.280
ANNOUNCER:
And the ball's up.

01:04:46.083 --> 01:04:47.415
[ Cheers and applause ]

01:04:50.287 --> 01:04:53.188
[ Cheers and applause
continues ]

01:04:57.227 --> 01:05:00.428
Joey Kalay catches the ball
on the slant for a touchdown.

01:05:00.430 --> 01:05:03.198
Saints win.
Saints win!

01:05:03.200 --> 01:05:05.033
- Yes!
- Whoo-hoo!

01:05:05.035 --> 01:05:07.369
That's what I'm talking about!

01:05:07.371 --> 01:05:08.904
- Whoo!
- Thanks, buddy.

01:05:08.906 --> 01:05:11.640
Get!

01:05:15.412 --> 01:05:17.979
[ Slow music plays ]

01:05:33.230 --> 01:05:36.031
[ Woman vocalizing ]

01:05:56.353 --> 01:05:58.620
What are you doing here?

01:05:58.622 --> 01:06:00.355
BRITTANY:
What are <i> you</i> doing here?

01:06:00.357 --> 01:06:04.392
Um, Coach set me up
with a, um...

01:06:07.397 --> 01:06:10.298
I think we got set up together.

01:06:13.637 --> 01:06:15.570
Oh.

01:06:15.572 --> 01:06:17.072
Okay.

01:06:17.074 --> 01:06:19.207
'Cause Darrell asked me to come.

01:06:19.209 --> 01:06:22.310
He said it was for a game
or something.

01:06:22.312 --> 01:06:24.612
- RICH: Mm.
- [ Chuckles ]

01:06:26.116 --> 01:06:28.116
You hungry?

01:06:29.186 --> 01:06:31.619
Mm. [ Chuckles ]

01:06:31.621 --> 01:06:34.656
So, you hid in a dirty locker
for an hour?

01:06:34.658 --> 01:06:36.624
- I had no choice.
- [ Laughs ]

01:06:36.626 --> 01:06:39.694
I was a freshman being stuffed
into a freshman's locker...

01:06:39.696 --> 01:06:41.463
so that when he would
come by and open it,

01:06:41.465 --> 01:06:43.398
I would jump out
and scare the crap out of him.

01:06:43.400 --> 01:06:47.402
- [ Laughs ]
- That was like a ritual

01:06:47.404 --> 01:06:49.137
to be welcomed on the team.

01:06:49.139 --> 01:06:50.705
We all had to go through it,
but...

01:06:50.707 --> 01:06:53.675
That's so cruel.

01:06:53.677 --> 01:06:56.578
Oh, but so funny.

01:06:57.214 --> 01:06:58.713
- Oh, thank you.
- Thanks.

01:06:58.715 --> 01:07:01.249
You're welcome. Would you like
some wine with that?

01:07:01.251 --> 01:07:03.651
Uh, no, thank you.

01:07:03.653 --> 01:07:05.387
Thanks, though.

01:07:13.730 --> 01:07:15.463
You must feel invincible.

01:07:17.167 --> 01:07:19.100
Sorry?

01:07:19.770 --> 01:07:22.103
Just being in love.

01:07:22.739 --> 01:07:26.474
I think it's...
got to, single-handedly, be

01:07:26.476 --> 01:07:29.244
one of the best feelings
in the world...

01:07:29.246 --> 01:07:32.747
to be able to have
that one person, your soul mate.

01:07:32.749 --> 01:07:35.517
Someone you would walk
through the pits of hell

01:07:35.519 --> 01:07:38.086
just to be with them
at the end of the day.

01:07:41.158 --> 01:07:43.391
Makes you feel invincible.

01:07:45.796 --> 01:07:47.328
I want that.

01:07:47.330 --> 01:07:50.065
I just don't know
if she's out there for me.

01:07:50.700 --> 01:07:53.635
Or if I can...

01:07:53.637 --> 01:07:57.605
even make someone
feel invincible.

01:07:57.607 --> 01:08:00.575
I bet your fiancÃ©
feels that way.

01:08:01.845 --> 01:08:03.511
I'm sure he does.

01:08:12.456 --> 01:08:14.355
I'm sorry.

01:08:15.192 --> 01:08:16.758
Wait.

01:08:21.698 --> 01:08:23.865
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

01:09:17.254 --> 01:09:20.654
Hello, Richard. I'm Dr. Ng,
your neuro-oncologist.

01:09:20.657 --> 01:09:21.823
May I have a word?

01:09:23.827 --> 01:09:26.194
You responded very well
to the chemo treatments --

01:09:26.196 --> 01:09:29.163
shrinking the tumor
down to an appropriate size.

01:09:29.166 --> 01:09:31.832
Based on the test results,
we feel we can move forward

01:09:31.835 --> 01:09:33.568
with preparations
for your surgery.

01:09:34.537 --> 01:09:36.470
Okay.

01:09:36.473 --> 01:09:37.738
What about Darrell?

01:09:38.875 --> 01:09:40.774
I can't discuss that right now.

01:09:41.511 --> 01:09:42.911
Why? Just...

01:09:42.912 --> 01:09:44.845
At least tell me
he's gonna be okay.

01:09:44.848 --> 01:09:48.283
Every patient responds
differently to treatment.

01:09:48.285 --> 01:09:51.819
Unfortunately, for some,
surgery is not an option.

01:09:51.821 --> 01:09:55.190
Richard,
I know you two are close.

01:09:55.959 --> 01:10:00.295
Darrell, he may not make it
to Christmas.

01:10:00.297 --> 01:10:02.964
I'm going to speak
with his mother next.

01:11:06.696 --> 01:11:10.031
"The Lord is my shepherd.
I shall not want.

01:11:10.033 --> 01:11:12.800
He makes me lie down
in green pastures.

01:11:12.802 --> 01:11:15.470
He leads me besides
still waters.

01:11:15.472 --> 01:11:17.772
He restores my soul.

01:11:18.541 --> 01:11:20.541
He leads me
in paths of righteousness

01:11:20.543 --> 01:11:22.677
for his name's sake.

01:11:23.980 --> 01:11:27.882
Even though I walk through the
valley of the shadow of death...

01:11:28.551 --> 01:11:30.685
...I shall fear no evil,

01:11:30.687 --> 01:11:32.854
for you are with me.

01:11:34.291 --> 01:11:36.724
Your rod and staff comfort me.

01:11:38.328 --> 01:11:41.996
You set a table before me
in front of my enemies.

01:11:41.998 --> 01:11:44.565
You anoint my head with oil.

01:11:44.567 --> 01:11:46.934
My cup overflows.

01:11:47.871 --> 01:11:51.839
Indeed, goodness and mercy
will pursue me

01:11:51.841 --> 01:11:54.709
in all the days of my life.

01:11:54.711 --> 01:11:57.912
I will dwell in the house
of the Lord forever."

01:12:37.654 --> 01:12:40.555
[ Soft piano music plays ]

01:12:58.375 --> 01:13:00.708
[ Music continues ]

01:13:10.653 --> 01:13:11.986
Is that Logan's song?

01:13:11.988 --> 01:13:15.089
[ Music stops ]

01:13:37.514 --> 01:13:39.514
RICH: Do you know?

01:13:41.985 --> 01:13:43.718
Yeah.

01:13:47.557 --> 01:13:48.890
You all right?

01:13:51.561 --> 01:13:54.028
I've had time to accept it.

01:13:56.599 --> 01:13:59.734
My first love, Dom...

01:14:00.203 --> 01:14:02.537
...my fiancÃ©...

01:14:03.506 --> 01:14:04.872
...he took his own life.

01:14:07.510 --> 01:14:09.677
And...

01:14:10.680 --> 01:14:15.650
...I kept thinking
that it was my fault.

01:14:17.654 --> 01:14:22.156
Like I could have done something
to help him, you know?

01:14:24.828 --> 01:14:29.997
But then, I realized
that he just lost hope...

01:14:30.733 --> 01:14:32.934
...in himself...

01:14:34.204 --> 01:14:36.537
...in the world.

01:14:39.876 --> 01:14:41.876
He was sick.

01:14:44.013 --> 01:14:47.515
And it could have been
anyone else.

01:14:50.186 --> 01:14:51.986
So...

01:14:51.988 --> 01:14:54.956
that's why I became a nurse.

01:14:54.958 --> 01:15:00.995
To help illness, any illness,
and to...

01:15:02.832 --> 01:15:05.566
...and to help me
forgive myself.

01:15:12.842 --> 01:15:14.275
It's not easy, I tell you.

01:15:14.277 --> 01:15:17.144
I'm trying.
I am.

01:15:17.146 --> 01:15:19.013
But...

01:15:20.984 --> 01:15:23.284
...we just got to have faith.

01:15:23.286 --> 01:15:29.257
And that's when
we start healing.

01:15:34.931 --> 01:15:36.864
I don't know where God is

01:15:36.866 --> 01:15:39.200
or if he's even listening.

01:15:42.138 --> 01:15:44.038
You know, when Jesus
was crucified,

01:15:44.040 --> 01:15:47.141
his disciples
felt the same way.

01:15:48.044 --> 01:15:51.646
I mean, 'cause they felt
that he wasn't there.

01:15:51.648 --> 01:15:52.880
They couldn't see him.

01:15:52.882 --> 01:15:55.883
They couldn't feel him.

01:15:56.553 --> 01:16:00.087
Then, one day,
they went fishing.

01:16:00.089 --> 01:16:02.890
Caught nothing the entire day.

01:16:03.326 --> 01:16:10.298
And there was this man
on the shore that shouts,

01:16:10.300 --> 01:16:11.999
"Cast your nets
on the other side,"

01:16:12.001 --> 01:16:14.068
and that was what they did.

01:16:14.070 --> 01:16:18.172
And they caught so much fish.

01:16:19.909 --> 01:16:25.279
And then they realized
that it was him.

01:16:25.281 --> 01:16:31.986
Still watching and still
helping from a distance.

01:16:33.156 --> 01:16:35.690
And then one of his disciples
was so happy

01:16:35.692 --> 01:16:38.926
that he jumped off the boat
and swam towards him.

01:16:40.663 --> 01:16:42.663
How far did he swim?

01:16:45.268 --> 01:16:47.635
100 yards.

01:16:55.044 --> 01:16:57.812
So don't give up on yourself.

01:16:57.814 --> 01:16:59.614
All right?

01:17:13.963 --> 01:17:15.796
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:17:25.975 --> 01:17:28.009
Hey.

01:17:28.878 --> 01:17:30.177
Are you in pain?

01:17:30.980 --> 01:17:34.882
[ Paper rustling ]

01:17:35.351 --> 01:17:37.852
"Smile at everyone I see
for one whole day."

01:17:39.656 --> 01:17:41.389
Mm. [ Chuckles ]

01:17:41.391 --> 01:17:43.391
How's that going?

01:17:43.393 --> 01:17:45.760
Much better
now that you're here.

01:17:55.338 --> 01:17:59.807
Been sober for a month,
and I have not complained today.

01:18:02.245 --> 01:18:04.278
All right.

01:18:05.815 --> 01:18:07.982
You're in the red zone.

01:18:07.984 --> 01:18:09.216
Oh, I am.

01:18:09.218 --> 01:18:10.951
That's 'cause I'm awesome.

01:18:10.953 --> 01:18:13.154
I'm almost done
with my painting.

01:18:13.156 --> 01:18:15.322
One more, and we'll be tied.

01:18:15.324 --> 01:18:17.425
Yeah?
What are you painting?

01:18:17.427 --> 01:18:22.163
My friend who helped me make
this game, "100 Yards of Life."

01:18:23.366 --> 01:18:24.699
RICH:
All right, so, this card

01:18:24.701 --> 01:18:26.867
- reads that...
- Don't!

01:18:26.869 --> 01:18:29.003
Red-zone plays are secret.

01:18:30.406 --> 01:18:32.373
Okay.

01:18:32.375 --> 01:18:34.809
How about we get you
in the red zone?

01:18:38.948 --> 01:18:40.081
[ Door opens ]

01:18:40.817 --> 01:18:43.417
Yeah!
That was perfect.

01:18:43.419 --> 01:18:44.952
That was perfect.

01:18:44.954 --> 01:18:47.188
All right.
Give me another one of those.

01:18:52.361 --> 01:18:55.196
Are you sure
you haven't thrown before?

01:18:55.198 --> 01:18:57.231
Here it comes.

01:18:57.934 --> 01:18:59.967
Good job.
That was perfect.

01:18:59.969 --> 01:19:02.269
They could be brothers.
[ Chuckles ]

01:19:02.271 --> 01:19:03.938
- Thanks.
- RICH: All right, you ready?

01:19:03.940 --> 01:19:07.007
- Here we go.
- I'm happy for that.

01:19:07.009 --> 01:19:08.843
I didn't know
what to think about Rich,

01:19:08.845 --> 01:19:12.146
but Darrell loves him.

01:19:12.148 --> 01:19:16.050
Rich is a good kid.
He's just misunderstood.

01:19:16.052 --> 01:19:18.853
- And Darrell, he's so bright.
- RICH: All right, here we go.

01:19:18.855 --> 01:19:23.858
When he was about 8, his cancer
took a turn for the worse.

01:19:23.860 --> 01:19:27.194
He had a seizure that put him
in a three-day coma.

01:19:27.196 --> 01:19:31.866
When he woke up from his coma,
he was a different little boy.

01:19:32.435 --> 01:19:34.301
What about you, Berry?

01:19:34.303 --> 01:19:37.104
- Any family?
- [ Chuckles ]

01:19:37.106 --> 01:19:38.773
Football.

01:19:38.775 --> 01:19:41.208
My team is my family.

01:19:41.210 --> 01:19:44.445
And, right now, I got a boy
fighting for his life,

01:19:44.447 --> 01:19:45.446
just like you.

01:19:45.448 --> 01:19:48.415
Yes!
That was perfect.

01:19:48.417 --> 01:19:50.484
And I think we're tied now.

01:19:50.486 --> 01:19:53.053
That's what I'm talking about.

01:20:09.939 --> 01:20:11.272
Hey, little man.

01:20:11.274 --> 01:20:12.506
We got you a little something.

01:20:12.508 --> 01:20:14.542
Christmas came early.

01:20:14.544 --> 01:20:18.012
Yeah, well, I knew a guy, who
knows a guy, who knows Santa.

01:20:18.014 --> 01:20:19.914
[ Chuckles ]

01:20:23.019 --> 01:20:24.485
Well, who's it from?

01:20:24.487 --> 01:20:27.254
It's from the board
of hospitals in Cebu.

01:20:27.256 --> 01:20:29.089
Yeah?
What's it say?

01:20:29.091 --> 01:20:32.026
They heard about the game,
and they want to sponsor it

01:20:32.028 --> 01:20:35.129
to hospitals
all over the Philippines.

01:20:35.131 --> 01:20:37.998
And when you get better,
you can present the game

01:20:38.000 --> 01:20:40.167
to foundations
all over the world.

01:20:40.169 --> 01:20:42.837
It's gonna help so many people.

01:20:42.839 --> 01:20:44.839
DARRELL: People like us.

01:20:45.541 --> 01:20:49.109
And when we're both out
of the hospital, I promise --

01:20:49.111 --> 01:20:51.879
We'll help heal the world
together.

01:20:51.881 --> 01:20:53.380
All right?

01:20:53.382 --> 01:20:55.416
Come here.

01:20:55.418 --> 01:20:57.885
- We did it.
- No.

01:20:58.354 --> 01:20:59.520
<i>You</i> did it.

01:21:05.494 --> 01:21:08.095
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

01:21:19.475 --> 01:21:20.875
BRITTANY:
How are you feeling?

01:21:20.877 --> 01:21:22.343
Good.

01:21:25.348 --> 01:21:28.616
- [ Breathes sharply ]
- Sorry.

01:21:30.253 --> 01:21:33.020
All right.

01:21:35.124 --> 01:21:36.457
- I can walk.
- Hmm?

01:21:36.459 --> 01:21:37.958
I can walk.

01:21:37.960 --> 01:21:39.660
Okay.

01:21:40.296 --> 01:21:43.163
Slowly. Okay.

01:21:56.445 --> 01:21:58.279
Oh.

01:21:58.281 --> 01:22:00.080
You okay?

01:22:01.550 --> 01:22:04.251
- [ Breathes deeply ]
- Okay.

01:22:04.253 --> 01:22:07.187
Let's just take a seat, okay?

01:22:11.227 --> 01:22:13.594
Okay.

01:22:13.596 --> 01:22:15.396
It's okay.

01:22:19.435 --> 01:22:21.135
RICH: [ Sighs ]

01:23:25.201 --> 01:23:27.234
You need to come check this out.

01:23:37.279 --> 01:23:38.312
That's impossible.

01:23:38.314 --> 01:23:40.714
No.
I saw him do it.

01:23:46.088 --> 01:23:48.288
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

01:23:49.358 --> 01:23:51.525
- [ Cellphone beeps ]
- Hello?

01:23:52.261 --> 01:23:54.228
Okay.

01:23:54.230 --> 01:23:56.196
You got an address?

01:23:57.533 --> 01:24:00.100
Okay, got it.

01:24:00.102 --> 01:24:01.769
Thanks.

01:24:02.471 --> 01:24:04.505
I got a lead on your mom.

01:24:07.276 --> 01:24:09.309
Can I go with you?

01:24:09.311 --> 01:24:10.811
Please.

01:24:12.448 --> 01:24:14.681
Okay. Come on.

01:24:33.269 --> 01:24:35.202
Nothing.

01:24:36.072 --> 01:24:37.304
All right.
Let's go back.

01:24:37.306 --> 01:24:38.605
Wait. No.
One more. Please.

01:24:38.607 --> 01:24:40.174
No, it's late.
You're exhausted.

01:24:40.176 --> 01:24:41.642
[ Sighs ] One more?

01:24:41.644 --> 01:24:44.278
- I need to keep looking.
- You need rest.

01:24:44.280 --> 01:24:45.612
I'm taking you
back to the hospital.

01:24:45.614 --> 01:24:47.381
I'm not giving up.

01:24:47.383 --> 01:24:49.149
We're not giving up.

01:24:49.151 --> 01:24:51.418
But being stressed right now
isn't good for you.

01:24:51.420 --> 01:24:53.754
We can do this another time.

01:24:53.756 --> 01:24:56.657
I don't have any more time!

01:24:57.293 --> 01:24:59.226
I'm losing everything.

01:24:59.228 --> 01:25:02.362
We fight together as a team.
Remember?

01:25:02.798 --> 01:25:05.232
I can't lose you, kid.

01:25:09.271 --> 01:25:11.839
What about Jeremiah?
He can throw for me.

01:25:11.841 --> 01:25:14.441
I'm not talking about
the football team.

01:25:14.443 --> 01:25:16.810
I'm talking about life.

01:25:16.812 --> 01:25:18.212
Your mom was a good friend
to me,

01:25:18.214 --> 01:25:19.646
and I want to find her, too.

01:25:19.648 --> 01:25:21.782
But, right now, you need rest

01:25:21.784 --> 01:25:23.817
so you can fight
your own battles.

01:25:26.789 --> 01:25:29.323
Every road leads to a dead end.

01:25:29.325 --> 01:25:31.758
You honestly think
I'm gonna find her?

01:25:31.760 --> 01:25:35.262
We have to keep the faith
that we eventually will.

01:25:35.264 --> 01:25:38.699
This game is far from over
for you, young man.

01:25:38.701 --> 01:25:41.735
God is closer than you think,
and I need you to see that.

01:25:55.718 --> 01:25:57.584
Can't sleep?

01:26:06.562 --> 01:26:09.596
The woman that helped you create
"100 Yards of Life"...

01:26:10.366 --> 01:26:12.766
...was she a volunteer
at the hospital?

01:26:19.875 --> 01:26:22.609
[ Paper rustling ]

01:26:30.386 --> 01:26:31.718
This is her.

01:26:31.720 --> 01:26:33.854
This is my friend.

01:26:39.395 --> 01:26:41.528
Can you tell me about her?

01:26:50.239 --> 01:26:52.372
Hi. Um...

01:26:54.643 --> 01:26:56.543
- Mm.
- Mm!

01:26:59.982 --> 01:27:01.748
Okay.

01:27:01.750 --> 01:27:04.218
[ Chuckles ]
I know what you need.

01:27:09.625 --> 01:27:11.391
[ Engine starts ]

01:27:13.229 --> 01:27:14.361
[ Engine starts ]

01:27:20.569 --> 01:27:22.703
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

01:27:27.309 --> 01:27:28.809
[ Engine shuts off ]

01:28:17.493 --> 01:28:19.826
What are you doing, Tess?

01:28:19.828 --> 01:28:23.730
- Were you following me?
- I'm doing my job, Tess --

01:28:23.732 --> 01:28:25.599
trying to find the truth.

01:28:25.601 --> 01:28:27.534
The truth?

01:28:27.536 --> 01:28:30.003
All you care about
is the big story and money.

01:28:30.005 --> 01:28:31.705
What is that in your hand?

01:28:31.707 --> 01:28:33.874
- Is that drugs?
- We are not having

01:28:33.876 --> 01:28:35.509
- this conversation.
- 'Cause it looked to me

01:28:35.511 --> 01:28:36.743
like you were about
to accidentally drop it

01:28:36.745 --> 01:28:37.844
in somebody else's house.

01:28:37.846 --> 01:28:39.012
This is none of your business.

01:28:39.014 --> 01:28:41.415
No, it <i> is</i> my business, Tess!

01:28:41.417 --> 01:28:43.984
It became my business when
you lied to me on the record

01:28:43.986 --> 01:28:45.752
and I put that lie in print.

01:28:45.754 --> 01:28:47.020
It became my business.

01:28:47.022 --> 01:28:48.622
I do what I need to do!

01:28:48.624 --> 01:28:51.458
Does that include
faking a facial accident

01:28:51.460 --> 01:28:52.759
and fabricating assault?

01:28:52.761 --> 01:28:54.594
Does it include that, Tess?

01:28:54.596 --> 01:28:55.796
Does it?

01:28:55.798 --> 01:28:57.964
It's easy for you to stand there

01:28:57.966 --> 01:29:00.334
and judge me
with your fancy watch.

01:29:01.370 --> 01:29:06.039
You have no idea
what my life is like.

01:29:06.041 --> 01:29:08.408
You get to fly home first class

01:29:08.410 --> 01:29:11.545
to your beautiful home
and nice car.

01:29:11.547 --> 01:29:13.680
[ Speaks native language ]

01:29:13.682 --> 01:29:15.816
I have nothing.

01:29:15.818 --> 01:29:19.653
And I do what I need to do
for my family to survive.

01:29:19.655 --> 01:29:22.389
You didn't have to do this,
Tess.

01:29:22.391 --> 01:29:24.057
You wouldn't pay me
for the story,

01:29:24.059 --> 01:29:25.759
so I went to a magazine
who would,

01:29:25.761 --> 01:29:27.994
and they gave me
really good money.

01:29:27.996 --> 01:29:29.096
RAY:
But you made it up.

01:29:29.098 --> 01:29:31.031
You lied.

01:29:31.033 --> 01:29:33.133
And now you're here,
trying to plant evidence

01:29:33.135 --> 01:29:34.868
to support that lie.

01:29:34.870 --> 01:29:36.069
It's just a story.

01:29:36.071 --> 01:29:38.004
Tess, it's a life!

01:29:38.006 --> 01:29:40.073
It's a good life.

01:29:40.075 --> 01:29:42.142
Christ, it's a life
you're trying to ruin.

01:29:42.144 --> 01:29:43.443
Don't you get that?

01:29:43.445 --> 01:29:46.713
What about <i> my</i> life?

01:29:47.383 --> 01:29:49.383
He never laid a hand on you,
did he?

01:29:49.385 --> 01:29:51.785
Hitting myself with that stone
was easy

01:29:51.787 --> 01:29:55.522
compared to the life
that I have to live.

01:29:55.524 --> 01:29:58.058
I deserve the life
that Rich threw away.

01:29:59.628 --> 01:30:00.761
[ Voice breaking ]
I need it.

01:30:06.802 --> 01:30:09.669
Please, just go home.

01:30:09.671 --> 01:30:10.971
They'll never believe you, Tess.

01:30:10.973 --> 01:30:13.039
Not in a million years.

01:30:15.110 --> 01:30:16.910
Really?

01:30:16.912 --> 01:30:18.945
Really.

01:30:25.687 --> 01:30:27.554
- [ Tape recorder beeps ]
- TESS: <i> Hitting myself</i>

01:30:27.556 --> 01:30:29.689
<i>with that stone was easy
compared to</i>

01:30:29.691 --> 01:30:31.925
<i>- the life that I have to live.</i>
- What's going on?

01:30:31.927 --> 01:30:34.661
Well, I guess I got
what I came here for.

01:30:36.165 --> 01:30:38.598
The truth.

01:30:41.937 --> 01:30:44.738
- [ Door opens ]
- Wait.

01:30:44.740 --> 01:30:46.006
Wait!

01:30:49.645 --> 01:30:51.745
Wait!

01:30:52.648 --> 01:30:54.948
Tess Sulay.

01:30:54.950 --> 01:30:56.950
- You're under arrest.
- [ Crying ]

01:30:56.952 --> 01:30:58.718
You have the right
to remain silent.

01:30:59.488 --> 01:31:01.455
Any statement you make
may be used against you

01:31:01.457 --> 01:31:02.889
in a court of law
in the Philippines.

01:31:02.891 --> 01:31:04.925
[ Tess sobs ]

01:31:50.873 --> 01:31:53.507
Did you send Juan?

01:31:53.509 --> 01:31:55.642
TESS: No.

01:31:56.612 --> 01:31:59.513
He saw my face and reacted.

01:32:02.851 --> 01:32:05.519
I tried to stop him.

01:32:10.759 --> 01:32:12.859
I didn't want you to get hurt.

01:32:13.695 --> 01:32:15.128
Just my reputation, right?

01:32:15.130 --> 01:32:16.963
No.

01:32:19.167 --> 01:32:22.569
- I did horrible things.
- You did horrible things to me.

01:32:23.605 --> 01:32:25.705
And for what?

01:32:25.707 --> 01:32:27.040
Your own gain?

01:32:28.577 --> 01:32:31.177
But you know what I realized?

01:32:34.616 --> 01:32:37.751
I realized I never really
treated you that well.

01:32:41.723 --> 01:32:44.891
I'm sorry I wasn't able
to give you what you wanted.

01:32:46.662 --> 01:32:50.664
And I'm sorry
for pushing you into doing this.

01:32:51.867 --> 01:32:53.700
No.

01:32:57.039 --> 01:32:59.005
<i>I'm</i> sorry.

01:33:00.642 --> 01:33:05.278
I was just hurt and confused.

01:33:06.715 --> 01:33:09.115
I ruined everything.

01:33:10.686 --> 01:33:13.186
And I hurt people that I love.

01:33:14.056 --> 01:33:15.622
Why?

01:33:15.624 --> 01:33:18.592
[ Voice breaking ]
Because I'm selfish.

01:33:21.763 --> 01:33:25.098
And because when I felt like
I was losing you...

01:33:25.801 --> 01:33:28.034
...I fought...

01:33:29.104 --> 01:33:31.805
...but I was just scared.

01:33:38.614 --> 01:33:40.814
I'm ready to pay.

01:33:50.392 --> 01:33:51.825
You already did.

01:33:52.861 --> 01:33:55.228
I'm not pressing charges.

01:33:56.131 --> 01:33:58.231
You're free to go, Tess.

01:34:02.104 --> 01:34:04.704
What about the drugs?

01:34:05.874 --> 01:34:08.308
RICH: The police
never found any drugs.

01:34:10.779 --> 01:34:12.679
Rich.

01:34:17.686 --> 01:34:19.653
Bye, Tess.

01:34:29.431 --> 01:34:31.831
[ Thunder rumbling ]

01:34:34.202 --> 01:34:35.935
[ Vehicle door closes ]

01:35:06.702 --> 01:35:08.968
[ Slow music plays ]

01:35:13.341 --> 01:35:16.076
[ Woman vocalizing ]

01:35:36.131 --> 01:35:38.765
We'll be waiting for you
when you wake up.

01:35:40.068 --> 01:35:42.035
And we'll have ourselves
a good, old-fashioned barbecue

01:35:42.037 --> 01:35:43.937
waiting for you.

01:35:44.740 --> 01:35:45.905
And balut.

01:35:45.907 --> 01:35:48.808
Mmm. My favorite.

01:35:52.047 --> 01:35:53.413
Good luck, kuya.

01:35:53.415 --> 01:35:55.515
I'll see you soon, toto.

01:36:02.157 --> 01:36:04.124
Okay.

01:36:04.793 --> 01:36:06.793
[ Breathes deeply ]

01:36:08.864 --> 01:36:11.531
I wish my mom was here.

01:36:12.334 --> 01:36:14.267
I'll be by your side
the entire time.

01:36:14.269 --> 01:36:15.969
I promise.

01:36:16.805 --> 01:36:18.972
Making me feel invincible.

01:36:24.012 --> 01:36:26.546
[ Woman vocalizing ]

01:36:38.093 --> 01:36:39.859
DOCTOR:
The surgery went well.

01:36:39.861 --> 01:36:42.495
We managed to successfully
remove the tumor from his brain.

01:36:42.497 --> 01:36:44.097
However,
there were complications.

01:36:44.099 --> 01:36:45.965
BERRY: What happened?

01:36:45.967 --> 01:36:48.802
DOCTOR: During surgery, his
heart stopped for 7 1/2 minutes

01:36:48.804 --> 01:36:51.137
until we revived him.

01:36:51.139 --> 01:36:52.939
BERRY:
But he's okay, right?

01:36:52.941 --> 01:36:56.509
He's alive, but due to the loss
of oxygen to his brain,

01:36:56.511 --> 01:36:58.578
he slipped into a coma.

01:36:58.580 --> 01:37:00.814
It is too early to measure
the amount of damage

01:37:00.816 --> 01:37:03.416
he sustained
during those critical moments.

01:37:03.418 --> 01:37:09.222
But we do not know
when or if he'll ever wake.

01:37:09.224 --> 01:37:11.491
Kuya.

01:37:11.493 --> 01:37:15.562
They said you died,
but came back.

01:37:15.564 --> 01:37:18.565
[ Echoing ]
You saw it, too, didn't you?

01:37:18.567 --> 01:37:21.367
It's beautiful, isn't it?

01:37:22.604 --> 01:37:26.072
The colors, smells, the sounds.

01:37:26.074 --> 01:37:30.443
Did you see them, the people
glimmering with light?

01:37:31.580 --> 01:37:34.147
I'll see them again, too.

01:37:35.951 --> 01:37:38.284
When I came back
from that place,

01:37:38.286 --> 01:37:40.320
I could see them.

01:37:40.322 --> 01:37:42.989
People who were here
[Sniffles, Sobs]

01:37:42.991 --> 01:37:45.859
but became angels in the next.

01:37:48.897 --> 01:37:51.030
LOGAN: [ Echoing ] Ray!

01:37:52.067 --> 01:37:55.068
DARRELL: That's where I learned
that the world was sick,

01:37:55.070 --> 01:37:59.072
that we just can't see,
but we feel it.

01:37:59.074 --> 01:38:02.175
And now I know
why God sent me back.

01:38:02.177 --> 01:38:04.510
To help heal
more of his children

01:38:04.512 --> 01:38:07.347
that he loves so much.

01:38:07.349 --> 01:38:09.415
To serve.

01:38:09.417 --> 01:38:11.651
Your mom knew how.

01:38:11.653 --> 01:38:14.120
Now it's your turn, Rich.

01:38:14.122 --> 01:38:17.523
Please help them
any way you can.

01:38:17.525 --> 01:38:21.995
In this world, there's
no such thing as goodbye.

01:38:21.997 --> 01:38:23.663
Only [Speaking native language]

01:38:23.665 --> 01:38:24.998
It means...

01:38:25.000 --> 01:38:27.033
I'll see you soon.

01:38:49.424 --> 01:38:50.924
NURSE:
[ Speaking native language ]

01:38:50.926 --> 01:38:53.092
He's awake!
[ Speaks native language ]

01:39:05.206 --> 01:39:07.407
What about Darrell?

01:39:15.083 --> 01:39:17.050
[ Breathes sharply ]

01:39:37.105 --> 01:39:40.139
Our Father, who art in heaven,

01:39:40.141 --> 01:39:41.708
hallowed be thy name.

01:39:41.710 --> 01:39:44.177
Thy kingdom come.

01:39:44.179 --> 01:39:48.147
Thy will be done on Earth
as it is in heaven.

01:39:48.149 --> 01:39:52.385
Give us this day our daily bread
and forgive us our trespasses

01:39:52.387 --> 01:39:55.188
as we forgive those
who trespass against us.

01:39:55.690 --> 01:39:59.459
Lead us not into temptation,
but deliver us from evil.

01:39:59.461 --> 01:40:03.997
For thine is the kingdom and
the power and the glory forever.

01:40:04.466 --> 01:40:06.366
Amen.

01:40:29.724 --> 01:40:32.091
You saved my son's life.

01:40:33.228 --> 01:40:37.430
I knew you were a man
with a purpose to serve others.

01:40:37.432 --> 01:40:39.732
Just like Darrell.

01:41:11.299 --> 01:41:13.132
He won.

01:41:16.404 --> 01:41:20.640
Now serve with your new life.

01:41:20.642 --> 01:41:22.708
Help others in need.

01:41:22.710 --> 01:41:25.411
Be good to everyone...

01:41:25.413 --> 01:41:28.448
just as my son was.

01:42:08.690 --> 01:42:10.690
<i>Philadelphia selects...</i>

01:42:10.692 --> 01:42:13.226
<i>Kelly Barnum, linebacker.</i>

01:42:13.228 --> 01:42:15.761
[ Cheers and applause ]

01:42:15.763 --> 01:42:18.731
RAY:
The 100-yard triumph.

01:42:18.733 --> 01:42:20.867
Familiar to American football,

01:42:20.869 --> 01:42:23.369
when a team battles
for every yard

01:42:23.371 --> 01:42:28.407
until they reach
the 100-yard mark, a touchdown.

01:42:28.409 --> 01:42:30.743
The same saying
goes for another game,

01:42:30.745 --> 01:42:32.845
one developed by a child

01:42:32.847 --> 01:42:36.382
and played by those
who face true adversity.

01:42:36.384 --> 01:42:39.485
A game that requires
everyone to fight as a team

01:42:39.487 --> 01:42:43.756
and to fear nothing
in order to achieve everything,

01:42:43.758 --> 01:42:48.694
fighting for every yard
in order to truly live.

01:42:48.696 --> 01:42:51.464
This game
is "The 100 Yards of Life."

01:42:51.466 --> 01:42:53.266
A game played not only to heal

01:42:53.268 --> 01:42:55.434
the physical ailments
of the body,

01:42:55.436 --> 01:42:58.204
but the metaphorical cancers,
as well.

01:42:58.206 --> 01:43:00.806
Anger, regret...

01:43:01.743 --> 01:43:05.912
...addiction, grief, and fear...

01:43:06.548 --> 01:43:08.781
...are some of the many ailments
that hold us back

01:43:08.783 --> 01:43:11.551
from truly living our lives.

01:43:11.553 --> 01:43:14.387
More importantly,
it helps us to understand

01:43:14.389 --> 01:43:17.323
the second chances
that are given to us.

01:43:19.727 --> 01:43:22.395
Former Colorado quarterback
Richard Porter

01:43:22.397 --> 01:43:25.531
witnessed the power
of this game firsthand...

01:43:27.769 --> 01:43:29.468
...coming to the Philippines,

01:43:29.470 --> 01:43:31.571
facing darkness,
only to find light

01:43:31.573 --> 01:43:34.340
after making the triumph,
along with a dozen others

01:43:34.342 --> 01:43:37.276
the game touched
at St. Thomas Hospital.

01:43:41.349 --> 01:43:45.785
Now Richard Porter is
no longer pursuing football...

01:43:47.555 --> 01:43:49.922
...but something much bigger.

01:43:52.627 --> 01:43:54.493
Oftentimes in life,

01:43:54.495 --> 01:43:56.929
we believe when the clock
starts to run out,

01:43:56.931 --> 01:43:59.599
we think the game is over.

01:44:00.468 --> 01:44:03.269
But it's only
the second quarter.

01:44:16.918 --> 01:44:19.485
[ Toilet flushes ]

01:44:29.998 --> 01:44:31.497
[ Knock on door ]

01:44:36.004 --> 01:44:37.536
Hi.

01:44:37.538 --> 01:44:39.038
Hi.

01:44:39.841 --> 01:44:41.607
Come in.

01:44:45.647 --> 01:44:48.781
So, I got you...

01:44:48.783 --> 01:44:49.882
this.

01:44:59.794 --> 01:45:01.694
BRITTANY: Thank you.

01:45:06.434 --> 01:45:07.900
I think someone needs a haircut.

01:45:07.902 --> 01:45:09.869
[ Both chuckle ]

01:45:14.842 --> 01:45:17.810
Thank you for making me
feel invincible.

01:45:18.646 --> 01:45:20.880
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

01:45:29.724 --> 01:45:31.357
[ Cellphone beeps ]

01:45:31.359 --> 01:45:33.392
- Hello?
- HENRY: Hey, Rich.

01:45:33.394 --> 01:45:34.694
This is Henry.

01:45:34.696 --> 01:45:37.663
I received a call
from one of your leads.

01:45:37.665 --> 01:45:39.832
Are you sitting down?

01:45:43.705 --> 01:45:45.338
[ Cellphone beeps ]

01:46:33.454 --> 01:46:35.688
[ Slow piano music plays ]

01:47:26.574 --> 01:47:28.474
I know you.

01:47:32.447 --> 01:47:33.979
I'm your son.

01:47:37.852 --> 01:47:40.653
I'm sorry.
I...

01:47:40.655 --> 01:47:42.655
I don't...

01:47:44.992 --> 01:47:47.593
RICH: Shh. It's okay.

01:47:48.496 --> 01:47:50.095
I'm here now.

01:47:50.097 --> 01:47:52.164
Can I play you something?

01:47:58.206 --> 01:48:00.639
[ "Logan's Song" plays ]

01:48:56.764 --> 01:48:58.697
[ Slow music plays ]
